files.name: .editorconfig
files.content:
root = true

[*]
indent_style = space
indent_size = 4
end_of_line = lf
charset = utf-8
trim_trailing_whitespace = true
insert_final_newline = true

[*.md]
trim_trailing_whitespace = false

# Cache Configs
CACHE_STORE=database # Defaults to database. Other available cache store: redis and filesystem
REDIS_URL= # Redis URL - could be a local redis instance or cloud hosted redis. Also support rediss:// urls

# Discord Configuration
DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID=
DISCORD_API_TOKEN=              # Bot token
DISCORD_VOICE_CHANNEL_ID=       # The ID of the voice channel the bot should join (optional)

OPENAI_API_KEY=                 # OpenAI API key, starting with sk-
OPENAI_API_URL=                 # OpenAI API Endpoint (optional), Default: https://api.openai.com/v1

MEDIUM_OPENAI_MODEL=            # Default: gpt-4o
LARGE_OPENAI_MODEL=             # Default: gpt-4o

files.content:
tasks:
  - name: "init eliza env"
    init: |
      nvm install v23.3.0
      git fetch --tags
      git checkout $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0)
    command: pnpm install && pnpm run build

files.content:
# Changelog

## [v0.1.7](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/tree/v0.1.7) (2025-01-04)

[Full Changelog](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/compare/v0.1.7-alpha.2...v0.1.7)

**Implemented enhancements:**

- Implement Caching for API Responses [\#1794](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1794)
- Implement Caching for API Responses [\#1792](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1792)
- Implement Caching for API Responses [\#1791](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1791)
- Implement Caching for API Responses [\#1789](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1789)
- Feature Request: Implement Enhanced Error Logging for API Calls [\#1736](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1736)
- Implement feature for issue \#1725 on repository elizaOS/eliza branch develop [\#1734](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1734)
- Enhance API Documentation [\#1732](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1732)
- Implement feature for issue \#1725 [\#1731](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1731)
- Implement feature for issue \#1725 [\#1730](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1730)
- Enhance API Documentation [\#1729](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1729)
- Implement a Caching Mechanism for API Responses [\#1726](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1726)
- Implement a Structured Logging Framework [\#1724](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1724)
- Add support for Coinbase Commerce integration [\#1723](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1723)
- Serve docusaurus docs from a docker container for quick docs verification [\#1720](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1720)
- Use Caret \(^\) for Dependency Versions in package.json [\#1662](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1662)
- Deduplicate dependencies across plugins and move shared dependencies to the root package.json [\#1658](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1658)
- Deduplicate Dependencies Across Plugins [\#1656](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1656)
- Deduplicate Dependencies Across Plugins [\#1652](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1652)
- Deduplicate Dependencies Across Plugins [\#1650](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1650)
- Viem version too old to include Arthera EVM chain [\#1635](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1635)
- Add Spanish Translation for Documentation README \(docs/README\_es.md\) [\#1592](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1592)
- Expand Support for Non-OpenAI Models in Token Trimming [\#1565](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1565)
- spades [\#1563](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1563)
- Support better in-monorepo navigation with custom conditions [\#1363](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1363)
- Add Livepeer as an Image Generation Provider [\#1271](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1271)
- Arbitrum Integration [\#851](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/851)
- Twitter Spaces Voice Client [\#301](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/301)
- üêõ fix plugins.md formatting for docs with dockerized docs validation [\#1722](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/pull/1722) ([marcellodesales](https://github.com/marcellodesales))

**Fixed bugs:**

- Fix: Standardize ACTION\_INTERVAL unit to minutes in Twitter client [\#1788](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1788)
- pdf js crashes the agent [\#1751](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1751)
- Failed to run on Macbook M1 [\#1742](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1742)
- Issue Created: http proxy error: /e0e10e6f-ff2b-0d4c-8011-1fc1eee7cb32/message [\#1733](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1733)
- can't build framework - followed quick start - pnpm build error [\#1714](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1714)
- Google Model Not Working [\#1709](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1709)
- failed: @elizaos/plugin-echochambers\#build [\#1691](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1691)
- initial setup not working. help needed please. [\#1666](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1666)
- ImageDescriptionService  [\#1643](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1643)
- Dockerfile errors when building image [\#1623](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1623)
- Initial setup based on docs not working [\#1622](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1622)
- Running Eliza with LLAMALOCAL fails after first query [\#1575](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1575)
- Quick start guide bug - pnpm start [\#1552](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1552)
- callback throws - \["‚õî TypeError: callback is not a function"\] - when action is called from the Twitter Client [\#1544](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1544)
- Bug: generateText is ignoring dynamic parameters due to a hard-coded model class [\#1439](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1439)
- fix: Slack client Media type implementation missing required properties in message attachments [\#1384](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1384)
- Error when trying deploy using dockerfile [\#1168](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1168)

**Closed issues:**

- Pull Request Created: Simulate discord typing while generating a response [\#1786](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1786)
- Fix Public Solana Wallet Not Found! [\#1781](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1781)
- \<script src="https://gist.github.com/EToreo/2029242.js"\>\</script\> [\#1692](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/issues/1692)

**Merged pull requests:**

- chore: bump version to v.0.1.7 [\#1804](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/pull/1804) ([shakkernerd](https://github.com/shakkernerd))
- fix: generation tests for trimTokens [\#1803](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/pull/1803) ([shakkernerd](https://github.com/shakkernerd))
- chore: install with no frozen-lockfile flag [\#1802](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/pull/1802) ([shakkernerd](https://github.com/shakkernerd))
- Revert "fix\(postgres\): Handle vector extension creation properly \(\#1561\)" [\#1799](https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/pull/1799) ([shakkernerd](https://github.com/shakkernerd))

files.name: CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
files.content:
# Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We as members, contributors, and leaders pledge to make participation in our
community a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body
size, visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender
identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status,
nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity
and orientation.

We pledge to act and interact in ways that contribute to an open, welcoming,
diverse, inclusive, and healthy community.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment for our
community include:

* Demonstrating empathy and kindness toward other people
* Being respectful of differing opinions, viewpoints, and experiences
* Giving and gracefully accepting constructive feedback
* Accepting responsibility and apologizing to those affected by our mistakes,
  and learning from the experience
* Focusing on what is best not just for us as individuals, but for the
  overall community

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

* The use of sexualized language or imagery, and sexual attention or
  advances of any kind
* Trolling, insulting or derogatory comments, and personal or political attacks
* Public or private harassment
* Publishing others' private information, such as a physical or email
  address, without their explicit permission
* Other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a
  professional setting

## Enforcement Responsibilities

Community leaders are responsible for clarifying and enforcing our standards of
acceptable behavior and will take appropriate and fair corrective action in
response to any behavior that they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive,
or harmful.

Community leaders have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject
comments, commits, code, wiki edits, issues, and other contributions that are
not aligned to this Code of Conduct, and will communicate reasons for moderation
decisions when appropriate.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies within all community spaces, and also applies when
an individual is officially representing the community in public spaces.
Examples of representing our community include using an official e-mail address,
posting via an official social media account, or acting as an appointed
representative at an online or offline event.

## Enforcement

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be
reported to the community leaders responsible for enforcement at
[discord server](https://discord.gg/ai16z).
All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

All community leaders are obligated to respect the privacy and security of the
reporter of any incident.

## Enforcement Guidelines

Community leaders will follow these Community Impact Guidelines in determining
the consequences for any action they deem in violation of this Code of Conduct:

### 1. Correction

**Community Impact**: Use of inappropriate language or other behavior deemed
unprofessional or unwelcome in the community.

**Consequence**: A private, written warning from community leaders, providing
clarity around the nature of the violation and an explanation of why the
behavior was inappropriate. A public apology may be requested.

### 2. Warning

**Community Impact**: A violation through a single incident or series
of actions.

**Consequence**: A warning with consequences for continued behavior. No
interaction with the people involved, including unsolicited interaction with
those enforcing the Code of Conduct, for a specified period of time. This
includes avoiding interactions in community spaces as well as external channels
like social media. Violating these terms may lead to a temporary or
permanent ban.

### 3. Temporary Ban

**Community Impact**: A serious violation of community standards, including
sustained inappropriate behavior.

**Consequence**: A temporary ban from any sort of interaction or public
communication with the community for a specified period of time. No public or
private interaction with the people involved, including unsolicited interaction
with those enforcing the Code of Conduct, is allowed during this period.
Violating these terms may lead to a permanent ban.

### 4. Permanent Ban

**Community Impact**: Demonstrating a pattern of violation of community
standards, including sustained inappropriate behavior,  harassment of an
individual, or aggression toward or disparagement of classes of individuals.

**Consequence**: A permanent ban from any sort of public interaction within
the community.

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant][homepage],
version 2.0, available at
https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html.

Community Impact Guidelines were inspired by [Mozilla's code of conduct
enforcement ladder](https://github.com/mozilla/diversity).

[homepage]: https://www.contributor-covenant.org

For answers to common questions about this code of conduct, see the FAQ at
https://www.contributor-covenant.org/faq. Translations are available at
https://www.contributor-covenant.org/translations.

files.content:
# Contributing to Eliza

First off, thank you for considering contributing to Eliza! We welcome contributions from everyone, regardless of experience level.

## Contribution License Agreement

By contributing to Eliza, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the MIT License. This means:

1. You grant us (and everyone else) a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use your contributions.
2. Your contributions are and will be available as Free and Open Source Software (FOSS).
3. You have the right to submit the work under this license.
4. You understand that your contributions are public and that a record of the contribution is maintained indefinitely.

## The OODA Loop: A Framework for Contribution

We believe in the power of the OODA Loop - a decision-making framework that emphasizes speed and adaptability. OODA stands for:

- **Observe**: Gather information and insights about the project, the community, and the broader AI ecosystem.
- **Orient**: Analyze your observations to identify opportunities for contribution and improvement.
- **Decide**: Choose a course of action based on your analysis. This could be proposing a new feature, fixing a bug, or creating content.
- **Act**: Execute your decision and share your work with the community.

## How to Contribute

### For Developers

1. **Extend Eliza's Capabilities**

    - Develop new actions, evaluators, and providers
    - Improve existing components and modules

2. **Enhance Infrastructure**

    - Review open issues and submit PRs
    - Test and update documentation
    - Optimize performance
    - Improve deployment solutions

3. Fork the repo and create your branch from `main`.
    1. The name of the branch should start with the issue number and be descriptive of the changes you are making.
    2. Example: 9999--add-test-for-bug-123
4. If you've added code that should be tested, add tests.
5. Ensure the test suite passes.
6. Make sure your code lints.
7. Issue that pull request!

## Styleguides

### Git Commit Messages

- Use the present tense ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
- Use the imperative mood ("Move cursor to..." not "Moves cursor to...")
- Limit the first line to 72 characters or less
- Reference issues and pull requests liberally after the first line

### JavaScript Styleguide

- All JavaScript must adhere to [JavaScript Standard Style](https://standardjs.com/).

### TypeScript Styleguide

- All TypeScript must adhere to [TypeScript Standard Style](https://github.com/standard/ts-standard).

### Documentation Styleguide

- Use [Markdown](https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/) for documentation.

## Additional Notes

### Issue and Pull Request Labels

This section lists the labels we use to help us track and manage issues and pull requests.

- `bug` - Issues that are bugs.
- `enhancement` - Issues that are feature requests.
- `documentation` - Issues or pull requests related to documentation.
- `good first issue` - Good for newcomers.

## Getting Help

- Join [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z)
- Check [FAQ](docs/community/faq.md)
- Create GitHub issues

## Additional Resources

- [Local Development Guide](docs/guides/local-development.md)
- [Configuration Guide](docs/guides/configuration.md)
- [API Documentation](docs/api)

## Contributor Guide

Welcome to the Eliza contributor guide! This document is designed to help you understand how you can be part of building the future of autonomous AI agents, regardless of your technical background.

### Code of Conduct

#### Our Pledge

In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming environment, we as contributors and maintainers pledge to make participation in our project and our community a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

#### Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to creating a positive environment include:

- Using welcoming and inclusive language
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences
- Gracefully accepting constructive criticism
- Focusing on what is best for the community
- Showing empathy towards other community members

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- The use of sexualized language or imagery and unwelcome sexual attention or advances
- Trolling, insulting/derogatory comments, and personal or political attacks
- Public or private harassment
- Publishing others' private information without explicit permission
- Other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a professional setting

#### Our Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying the standards of acceptable behavior and are expected to take appropriate and fair corrective action in response to any instances of unacceptable behavior.

Project maintainers have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject comments, commits, code, wiki edits, issues, and other contributions that are not aligned to this Code of Conduct, or to ban temporarily or permanently any contributor for other behaviors that they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.

#### Scope

This Code of Conduct applies both within project spaces and in public spaces when an individual is representing the project or its community. Examples of representing a project or community include using an official project e-mail address, posting via an official social media account, or acting as an appointed representative at an online or offline event.

Thank you for contributing to Eliza and helping build the future of autonomous AI agents! üéâ

# Use a specific Node.js version for better reproducibility
FROM node:23.3.0-slim AS builder

# Install pnpm globally and install necessary build tools
RUN npm install -g pnpm@9.4.0 && \
    apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y git python3 make g++ && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Set Python 3 as the default python
RUN ln -s /usr/bin/python3 /usr/bin/python

# Set the working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy package.json and other configuration files
COPY package.json pnpm-lock.yaml pnpm-workspace.yaml .npmrc turbo.json ./

# Copy the rest of the application code
COPY agent ./agent
COPY packages ./packages
COPY scripts ./scripts
COPY characters ./characters

# Install dependencies and build the project
RUN pnpm install \
    && pnpm build-docker \
    && pnpm prune --prod

# Create a new stage for the final image
FROM node:23.3.0-slim

# Install runtime dependencies if needed
RUN npm install -g pnpm@9.4.0 && \
    apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y git python3 && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

WORKDIR /app

# Copy built artifacts and production dependencies from the builder stage
COPY --from=builder /app/package.json ./
COPY --from=builder /app/pnpm-workspace.yaml ./
COPY --from=builder /app/.npmrc ./
COPY --from=builder /app/turbo.json ./
COPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY --from=builder /app/agent ./agent
COPY --from=builder /app/packages ./packages
COPY --from=builder /app/scripts ./scripts
COPY --from=builder /app/characters ./characters

# Set the command to run the application
CMD ["pnpm", "start"]

# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1

## Modified version of https://docusaurus.community/knowledge/deployment/docker/

# Stage 1: Base image.
## Start with a base image containing NodeJS so we can build Docusaurus.
FROM node:23.3.0-slim AS base
## Disable colour output from yarn to make logs easier to read.

## https://pnpm.io/docker
ENV PNPM_HOME="/pnpm"
ENV PATH="$PNPM_HOME:$PATH"

ENV FORCE_COLOR=0
## Enable corepack.
RUN corepack enable
## Set the working directory to `/opt/docusaurus`.
WORKDIR /opt/docusaurus

## Required by docusaurus: [ERROR] Loading of version failed for version current
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git 

FROM base AS dev
## Set the working directory to `/opt/docusaurus`.
WORKDIR /opt/docusaurus
## Expose the port that Docusaurus will run on.
EXPOSE 3000
## Run the development server.
CMD [ -d "node_modules" ] && npm run start -- --host 0.0.0.0 --poll 1000 || pnpm install && pnpm run start -- --host 0.0.0.0 --poll 1000

# Stage 2b: Production build mode.
FROM base AS prod
## Set the working directory to `/opt/docusaurus`.
WORKDIR /opt/docusaurus

COPY docs/package.json /opt/docusaurus/package.json
COPY docs/package-lock.json /opt/docusaurus/package-lock.json

## Install dependencies with `--immutable` to ensure reproducibility.
RUN --mount=type=cache,id=pnpm,target=/pnpm/store pnpm install 

## Copy over the source code.
COPY docs/ /opt/docusaurus/
COPY packages/ /opt/packages/

## Required buy docusaurus [ERROR] Loading of version failed for version current
COPY .git/ /opt/.git/

# Build from sources
RUN pnpm run build

# Stage 3a: Serve with `docusaurus serve`.
FROM prod AS serve
## Expose the port that Docusaurus will run on.
EXPOSE 3000
## Run the production server.
CMD ["npm", "run", "serve", "--", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--no-open"]

## ‚ú® Features - üõ†Ô∏è Full-featured Discord, Twitter and Telegram connectors - üîó Support for every model (Llama, Grok, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) - üë• Multi-agent and room support - üìö Easily ingest and interact with your documents - üíæ Retrievable memory and document store - üöÄ Highly extensible - create your own actions and clients - ‚òÅÔ∏è Supports many models (local Llama, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq, etc.) - üì¶ Just works! ## Video Tutorials [AI Agent Dev School](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ArptLpQiKfI&list=PLx5pnFXdPTRzWla0RaOxALTSTnVq53fKL) ## üéØ Use Cases - ü§ñ Chatbots - üïµÔ∏è Autonomous Agents - üìà Business Process Handling - üéÆ Video Game NPCs - üß† Trading ## üí∞ If you plan to launch a token This framework is the number one open source project on github, we are enabling the next generation of human-machine interface but we still need your help to ensure the code is of the utmost quality with response rapid to critical issues that will affect our builder community at large. To ensure sustainable development and continued innovation, we ask contributions of 5-10% of initial token distributions from successful launches. All contributions are publicly tracked on-chain and used exclusively for ecosystem development. ### ‚ö†Ô∏è Don't forget to tip the big guy 10%: ‚ö†Ô∏è [AM84n1iLdxgVTAyENBcLdjXoyvjentTbu5Q6EpKV1PeG](https://solscan.io/account/AM84n1iLdxgVTAyENBcLdjXoyvjentTbu5Q6EpKV1PeG) ## üöÄ Quick Start ### Prerequisites - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) > **Note for Windows Users:** [WSL 2](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-manual) is required. ### Use the Starter (Recommended) ```bash git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza-starter.git cd eliza-starter cp .env.example .env pnpm i && pnpm build && pnpm start ``` Once the agent is running, you should see the message to run "pnpm start:client" at the end. Open another terminal and move to same directory and then run below command and follow the URL to chat to your agent. ```bash pnpm start:client ``` Then read the [Documentation](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/) to learn how to customize your Eliza. ### Manually Start Eliza (Only recommended if you know what you are doing) ```bash # Clone the repository git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza.git # Checkout the latest release # This project iterates fast, so we recommend checking out the latest release git checkout $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0) ``` ### Start Eliza with Gitpod [![Open in Gitpod](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/#https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/tree/main) ### Edit the .env file Copy .env.example to .env and fill in the appropriate values. ``` cp .env.example .env ``` Note: .env is optional. If you're planning to run multiple distinct agents, you can pass secrets through the character JSON Note: .env is optional. If you're planning to run multiple distinct agents, you can pass secrets through the character JSON ### Automatically Start Eliza This will run everything to set up the project and start the bot with the default character. ```bash sh scripts/start.sh ``` ### Edit the character file 1. Open `packages/core/src/defaultCharacter.ts` to modify the default character. Uncomment and edit. 2. To load custom characters: - Use `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` - Multiple character files can be loaded simultaneously 3. Connect with X (Twitter) - change `"clients": []` to `"clients": ["twitter"]` in the character file to connect with X ### Manually Start Eliza ```bash pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start # The project iterates fast, sometimes you need to clean the project if you are coming back to the project pnpm clean ``` #### Additional Requirements You may need to install Sharp. If you see an error when starting up, try installing it with the following command: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` ### Community & contact - [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/issues). Best for: bugs you encounter using Eliza, and feature proposals. - [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z). Best for: sharing your applications and hanging out with the community. - [Developer Discord](https://discord.gg/3f67SH4rXT). Best for: getting help and plugin development. ## Contributors ## Star History [![Star History Chart](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=elizaos/eliza&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#elizaos/eliza&Date)

üìñ [ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿπŸÑŸäŸÖÿßÿ™](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/) | üéØ [ÿßŸÑÿ£ŸÖÿ´ŸÑÿ©](https://github.com/thejoven/awesome-eliza)
## ‚ú® ŸÖÿß ŸáŸä ÿßŸÑŸÖŸäÿ≤ÿßÿ™ÿü - üõ†Ô∏è ÿßÿ™ÿµÿßŸÑÿßÿ™ ŸÖÿ¨Ÿáÿ≤ÿ© ÿ®ÿßŸÑŸÉÿßŸÖŸÑ ŸÑÿØŸäÿ≥ŸÉŸàÿ±ÿØÿå ÿ™ŸàŸäÿ™ÿ±ÿå Ÿàÿ™ŸäŸÑŸäÿ∫ÿ±ÿßŸÖ. - üë• ÿØÿπŸÖ ŸÖÿ™ÿπÿØÿØ ŸÑŸÑŸàŸÉŸÑÿßÿ° ŸàÿßŸÑÿ∫ÿ±ŸÅ. - üìö ÿßŸÑÿ™ŸÅÿßÿπŸÑ ÿ®ÿ•ÿ™ŸÇÿßŸÜ ŸÖÿπ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ≥ÿ™ŸÜÿØÿßÿ™ ŸÉŸÖÿß ŸäŸÖŸÉŸÜ ŸÅÿ≠ÿµŸáÿß ÿ®ÿ≥ŸáŸàŸÑÿ©. - üíæ ÿ∞ÿßŸÉÿ±ÿ© ŸÇŸàŸäÿ© ŸÇÿßÿ®ŸÑÿ© ŸÑÿßÿ≥ÿ™ÿ±ÿ¨ÿßÿπ ŸÖÿß ŸÅÿßÿ™ŸÉ! ŸàŸÉÿ∞ŸÑŸÉ ŸÖÿ≥ÿßÿ≠ÿ© ŸÉÿßŸÅŸäÿ© ŸÑŸÑÿ™ÿÆÿ≤ŸäŸÜ - üöÄ ÿ≥ÿ±Ÿäÿπÿ© ÿßŸÑÿßŸÜÿ™ÿ¥ÿßÿ± ÿ®ÿ¥ŸÉŸÑ ÿ∫Ÿäÿ± ŸÖÿ≥ÿ®ŸàŸÇÿå ŸáŸäŸëÿß! ÿ™ŸÅÿßÿπŸÑ ŸàÿßÿµŸÜÿπ ÿπŸÖŸÑÿßÿ° ÿÆÿßÿµŸäŸÜ ÿ®ŸÉ. - ‚òÅÔ∏è ÿ™ÿØÿπŸÖ ÿßŸÑÿπÿØŸäÿØ ŸÖŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÜŸÖÿßÿ∞ÿ¨ ŸÖÿ´ŸÑ:- - ŸÑÿßŸÖÿß (ŸÜŸÖŸàÿ∞ÿ¨ ŸÖŸÅÿ™Ÿàÿ≠ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿµÿØÿ± ŸÑŸÑÿ∞ŸÉÿßÿ° ÿßŸÑÿßÿµÿ∑ŸÜÿßÿπŸä Llama). - ÿ¨ÿ±ŸàŸÉ (ŸÜÿ∏ÿßŸÖ ÿ∞ŸÉÿßÿ° ÿßÿµÿ∑ŸÜÿßÿπŸä ŸÖÿ™ŸÇÿØŸÖ Grok). - ÿ£Ÿàÿ®ŸÜ ÿ•ŸäŸá ÿ¢Ÿä (OpenAI ŸÜŸÖÿßÿ∞ÿ¨ ÿ∞ŸÉÿßÿ° ÿßÿµÿ∑ŸÜÿßÿπŸä ŸÖÿ´ŸÑ ChatGPT). - ÿ£ŸÜÿ´ÿ±Ÿàÿ®ŸäŸÉ Anthropic Ÿàÿ∫Ÿäÿ±Ÿáÿß ŸÖŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÜŸÖÿßÿ∞ÿ¨ ÿßŸÑÿ£ÿÆÿ±Ÿâ! - üì¶ ÿ¨ÿßŸáÿ≤ÿ© ŸÑŸÑÿπŸÖŸÑ ÿ£Ÿä ŸàŸÇÿ™ Ÿàÿ®ÿ≥ŸáŸàŸÑÿ©! ## üéØ ŸÉŸäŸÅ ÿ≥ÿ™ŸÅŸäÿØŸÜŸäÿü - ü§ñ ÿ±Ÿàÿ®Ÿàÿ™ÿßÿ™ ÿßŸÑÿØÿ±ÿØÿ¥ÿ©. - üïµÔ∏è ŸàŸÉŸÑÿßÿ° ŸÖÿ≥ÿ™ŸÇŸÑŸàŸÜ. - üìà ÿ•ÿØÿßÿ±ÿ© ÿßŸÑÿ£ÿπŸÖÿßŸÑ. - üéÆ ŸÅŸä ÿßŸÑÿ¨ŸäŸÖŸäÿ≤ NPCs ÿ£Ÿà ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿßÿ™ ÿßŸÑÿ™Ÿä Ÿäÿ™ÿ≠ŸÉŸÖ ÿ®Ÿáÿß ÿßŸÑÿ≠ÿßÿ≥Ÿàÿ® ŸÅŸÇÿ∑ ŸàŸÑŸäÿ≥ ÿßŸÑŸÑÿßÿπÿ®. - üß† ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿØÿßŸàŸÑ. ## üöÄ ÿßÿ®ÿØÿ£ ÿßŸÑÿ¢ŸÜ! ### ŸÖÿßÿ∞ÿß ÿπŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ™ÿ∑ŸÑÿ®ÿßÿ™ ÿßŸÑÿ£ÿ≥ÿßÿ≥Ÿäÿ©ÿü - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) > **ŸÑŸÖÿ™ÿ≥ÿÆÿØŸÖŸä ÿßŸÑŸàŸäŸÜÿØŸàÿ≤ Ÿäÿ¨ÿ® ÿ£ŸÜ ŸäŸÉŸàŸÜ ŸÑÿØŸäŸÉ ŸÜÿ∏ÿßŸÖ ŸàŸäŸÜÿØŸàÿ≤ ÿßŸÑŸÅÿ±ÿπŸä ŸÑŸÑŸäŸÜŸÉÿ≥:** [WSL 2](https://learn.microsoft.com/de-de/windows/wsl/install-manual). ### ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ÿÆÿØÿßŸÖ ÿßŸÑŸÜÿ≥ÿÆÿ© ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ®ÿØÿ¶Ÿäÿ© (ŸÖŸàÿµŸâ ÿ®Ÿá) ```bash git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza-starter.git cp .env.example .env pnpm i && pnpm start ``` ÿ™ÿπŸÑŸÖ ÿ£ŸÉÿ´ÿ± ÿπŸÜ ŸÉŸäŸÅŸäÿ© ÿ™ÿÆÿµŸäÿµ ÿ•ŸÑŸäÿ≤ÿß ŸÖŸÜ ŸáŸÜÿß [ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿπŸÑŸäŸÖÿßÿ™](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/) ### ÿ•ÿ∞ÿß ŸÉÿßŸÜ ŸÑÿØŸäŸÉ ÿÆÿ®ÿ±ÿ© ÿ®ÿßŸÑŸÅÿπŸÑÿå ŸäŸèŸÖŸÉŸÜŸÉ ÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸäŸÑ ÿ•ŸÑŸäÿ≤ÿß ŸäÿØŸàŸäŸãÿß. ```bash # ÿßŸÜÿ¥ÿ¶ ŸÜÿ≥ÿÆÿ© git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza.git # ÿ£ŸÑŸÇ ŸÜÿ∏ÿ±ÿ© ÿπŸÑŸâ ÿ¢ÿÆÿ± ÿ™ÿ≠ÿØŸäÿ´ # Ÿáÿ∞ÿß ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿπ Ÿäÿ™ÿ∑Ÿàÿ± ÿ®ÿ≥ÿ±ÿπÿ©ÿå ŸÑÿ∞ÿßÿå ÿ£ŸàÿµŸäŸÉ ÿ®ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ÿÆÿØÿßŸÖ ÿ£ÿ≠ÿØÿ´ ÿ•ÿµÿØÿßÿ± git checkout $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0) ``` ### ÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸÑ ÿ•ŸÑŸäÿ≤ÿß ŸÖÿπ Gitpod [![In Gitpod √∂ffnen](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/#https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/tree/main) ### ÿπÿØŸëŸÑ ŸÖŸÑŸÅ .env-Datei ÿßŸÜÿ≥ÿÆ ŸÖŸÑŸÅ .env.example ÿ•ŸÑŸâ .env ŸàÿßŸÖŸÑÿ£ ÿßŸÑŸÇŸäŸÖ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸÜÿßÿ≥ÿ®ÿ©. ``` cp .env.example .env ``` ÿ∂ÿπ ŸÅŸä ÿßŸÑÿ•ÿπÿ™ÿ®ÿßÿ± ÿ£ŸÜ ŸÖŸÑŸÅ .env ÿßÿÆÿ™Ÿäÿßÿ±Ÿä. ÿ•ÿ∞ÿß ŸÉŸÜÿ™ ÿ™ÿÆÿ∑ÿ∑ ŸÑÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸäŸÑ ÿπÿØÿ© ŸàŸÉŸÑÿßÿ° ŸÖÿÆÿ™ŸÑŸÅŸäŸÜÿå ÿßÿ®ÿπÿ™ ÿßŸÑŸÄsecrets ŸÖŸÜ ÿÆŸÑÿßŸÑ ŸÖŸÑŸÅ JSON ÿßŸÑÿÆÿßÿµ ÿ®ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿ©. ### ÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸäŸÑ ÿ•ŸÑŸäÿ≤ÿß ÿ™ŸÑŸÇÿßÿ¶ŸäŸãÿß Ÿáÿ∞ÿß ÿßŸÑŸÉŸàÿØ ŸÑÿ™ŸÜŸÅŸäÿ∞ ÿ¨ŸÖŸäÿπ ÿßŸÑÿÆÿ∑Ÿàÿßÿ™ ÿßŸÑŸÑÿßÿ≤ŸÖÿ© ŸÑÿ•ÿπÿØÿßÿØ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿπ ŸàŸÉÿ∞ŸÑŸÉ ÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸäŸÑ ÿßŸÑÿ±Ÿàÿ®Ÿàÿ™ ŸÖÿπ ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿ© ÿßŸÑÿßŸÅÿ™ÿ±ÿßÿ∂Ÿäÿ©. ```bash sh scripts/start.sh ``` ### ŸÑÿ™ÿπÿØŸäŸÑ ŸÖŸÑŸÅ ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿ© ÿßŸÅÿ™ÿ≠ ŸÖŸÑŸÅ agent/src/character.ts ŸÑÿ™ÿπÿØŸäŸÑ ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿ© ÿßŸÑÿßŸÅÿ™ÿ±ÿßÿ∂Ÿäÿ©. ŸÇŸÖ ÿ®ÿ•ŸÑÿ∫ÿßÿ° ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿπŸÑŸäŸÇ ŸàÿπÿØŸëŸÑ ÿπŸÑŸäŸáÿß. ŸÑÿ™ÿ≠ŸÖŸäŸÑ ÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿßÿ™ ŸÖÿÆÿµÿµÿ© - ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ÿÆÿØŸÖ ÿßŸÑÿ£ŸÖÿ± "pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json - ŸäŸèŸÖŸÉŸÜŸÉ ÿ™ÿ≠ŸÖŸäŸÑ ÿπÿØÿ© ŸÖŸÑŸÅÿßÿ™ ŸÑŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿßÿ™ ŸÅŸä ŸÜŸÅÿ≥ ÿßŸÑŸàŸÇÿ™. ÿßŸÑÿßÿ™ÿµÿßŸÑ ÿ®ŸÄ X (ÿ™ŸàŸäÿ™ÿ±): - ÿ∫ŸäŸëÿ± "clients": [] ÿ•ŸÑŸâ "clients": ["twitter"] ŸÅŸä ŸÖŸÑŸÅ ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿ© ŸÑŸÑÿßÿ™ÿµÿßŸÑ ÿ®ŸÄ X ÿ£Ÿà ÿ™ŸàŸäÿ™ÿ± ### ŸÑÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸäŸÑ ÿ•ŸÑŸäÿ≤ÿß ŸäÿØŸàŸäŸãÿß ```bash pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start # ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿπ Ÿäÿ™ÿ∑Ÿàÿ± ÿ≥ÿ±ŸäÿπŸãÿß. ŸÑÿ∞ÿß ŸÇÿØ ÿ™ÿ≠ÿ™ÿßÿ¨ ÿ•ŸÑŸâ ÿ™ŸÜÿ∏ŸäŸÅ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿπ ÿ•ÿ∞ÿß ŸÇŸÖÿ™ ÿ®ÿßŸÑÿ±ÿ¨Ÿàÿπ ÿ•ŸÑŸäŸá ÿ®ÿπÿØ ŸÅÿ™ÿ±ÿ©. pnpm clean ``` #### ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ™ÿ∑ŸÑÿ®ÿßÿ™ ÿßŸÑÿ•ÿ∂ÿßŸÅŸäÿ© ŸÇÿØ ÿ™ÿ≠ÿ™ÿßÿ¨ ÿ•ŸÑŸâ ÿ™ÿ´ÿ®Ÿäÿ™ Sharp. ÿ•ÿ∞ÿß Ÿàÿßÿ¨Ÿáÿ™ ÿÆÿ∑ÿ£ ÿ£ÿ´ŸÜÿßÿ° ÿ®ÿØÿ° ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿ¥ÿ∫ŸäŸÑÿå ÿ¨ÿ±ÿ® ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ÿÆÿØÿßŸÖ ÿßŸÑÿ£ŸÖÿ± ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿßŸÑŸä: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` ### ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¨ÿ™ŸÖÿπ ŸàÿßŸÑÿØÿπŸÖ - ŸÅŸä ÿ≠ÿßŸÑ ÿ•ÿ∞ÿß Ÿàÿßÿ¨Ÿáÿ™ ÿ£Ÿä ŸÖÿ¥ÿßŸÉŸÑ ÿ™ÿ™ÿπŸÑŸÇ ÿ®ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ÿÆÿØÿßŸÖ ÿ•ŸÑŸäÿ≤ÿß ŸàŸÑÿ™ŸÇÿØŸäŸÖ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸÇÿ™ÿ±ÿ≠ÿßÿ™ [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/issues). - ŸÑŸÖÿ¥ÿßÿ±ŸÉÿ© ÿ™ÿ∑ÿ®ŸäŸÇÿßÿ™ŸÉ ŸàÿßŸÑÿ™ŸÅÿßÿπŸÑ ŸÖÿπ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¨ÿ™ŸÖÿπ [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z). ## ÿßŸÑŸÖŸèÿ≥ÿßŸáŸÖŸàŸÜ ## ÿ™ÿßÿ±ŸäÿÆ ÿßŸÑŸÜÿ¨ŸàŸÖ [![Star History Chart](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=elizaos/eliza&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#elizaos/eliza&Date)

files.content: # Eliza ## ÂäüËÉΩ - üõ† ÊîØÊåÅdiscord/Êé®Áâπ/telegramËøûÊé• - üë• ÊîØÊåÅÂ§öÊ®°ÊÄÅagent - üìö ÁÆÄÂçïÁöÑÂØºÂÖ•ÊñáÊ°£Âπ∂‰∏éÊñáÊ°£‰∫§‰∫í - üíæ ÂèØÊ£ÄÁ¥¢ÁöÑÂÜÖÂ≠òÂíåÊñáÊ°£Â≠òÂÇ® - üöÄ È´òÂèØÊãìÂ±ïÊÄßÔºå‰Ω†ÂèØ‰ª•Ëá™ÂÆö‰πâÂÆ¢Êà∑Á´ØÂíåË°å‰∏∫Êù•ËøõË°åÂäüËÉΩÊãìÂ±ï - ‚òÅÔ∏è Â§öÊ®°ÂûãÊîØÊåÅÔºåÂåÖÊã¨Llama„ÄÅOpenAI„ÄÅGrok„ÄÅAnthropicÁ≠â - üì¶ ÁÆÄÂçïÂ•ΩÁî® ‰Ω†ÂèØ‰ª•Áî®ElizaÂÅö‰ªÄ‰πàÔºü - ü§ñ ËÅäÂ§©Êú∫Âô®‰∫∫ - üïµÔ∏è Ëá™‰∏ªAgents - üìà ‰∏öÂä°ÊµÅÁ®ãËá™Âä®ÂåñÂ§ÑÁêÜ - üéÆ Ê∏∏ÊàèNPC # ÂºÄÂßã‰ΩøÁî® **ÂâçÁΩÆË¶ÅÊ±Ç(ÂøÖÈ°ª):** - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) ‰ª•‰∏ãÊòØ‰∏§ÁßçÂü∫Á°ÄÁöÑEliza‰∏ãËΩΩÊñπÊ°à, ËØ∑Ê†πÊçÆÊÉÖÂÜµËá™Ë°åÈÄâÊã©„ÄÇ ## (A) ‰ΩøÁî®ÂêØÂä®Âô®(Starter): Êé®Ëçê ``` git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza-starter.git cd eliza-starter cp .env.example .env ``` ## (B) ÊâãÂä®ÂêØÂä®Eliza: ‰ªÖÂú®ÊÇ®Áü•ÈÅìËá™Â∑±Âú®ÂÅö‰ªÄ‰πàÊó∂ÊâçÊé®Ëçê ``` git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza.git cd eliza # ÂàáÊç¢ÊúÄÊñ∞ÂèëÂ∏ÉÁöÑÁâàÊú¨(Checkout the latest release) # ElizaÁöÑËø≠‰ª£ÈÄüÂ∫¶ÈùûÂ∏∏Âø´, ÊâÄ‰ª•Êàë‰ª¨Âª∫ËÆÆÁªèÂ∏∏ÊÄßÁöÑÂàáÊç¢Âà∞ÊúÄÊñ∞ÁöÑÂèëÂ∏ÉÁâàÊú¨‰ª•ÂÖçÂá∫Áé∞ÈóÆÈ¢ò(This project iterates fast, so we recommend checking out the latest release) git checkout $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0) ``` Âú®Â∞Ü‰ª£Á†Å‰∏ãËΩΩÂà∞Êú¨Âú∞Âêé, Êàë‰ª¨Ë¶ÅÂÅö‰∏§‰ª∂‰∫ã: ### 1. ÁºñËæë.envÊñá‰ª∂(ÁéØÂ¢ÉÂèòÈáè) - Â∞Ü `.env.example` Â§çÂà∂‰∏∫ `.env` Âπ∂Âú®ÂÖ∂‰∏≠Â°´ÂÜôÈÄÇÂΩìÁöÑÂÄº - ÁºñËæëÊé®ÁâπÁéØÂ¢ÉÂπ∂ËæìÂÖ•‰Ω†ÁöÑÊé®ÁâπË¥¶Âè∑ÂíåÂØÜÁ†Å **ÊúÄÁÆÄÂåñÈÖçÁΩÆÊñπÊ°à**: ``` OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxx # ÈÖçÁΩÆOpenAI ÁöÑAPI, sk-ÂºÄÂ§¥, Ê≥®ÊÑè, ÁõÆÂâç‰∏çÊîØÊåÅAzureOpenAI! ## Â¶ÇÈÖçÁΩÆTwitter/X, ÂàôÈúÄÈÖçÁΩÆ # Twitter/X Configuration TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME=abc # Your Twitter/X account username TWITTER_PASSWORD=abc # Your Twitter/X account password TWITTER_EMAIL= xxx@gmail.com # Your Twitter/X account email TWITTER_COOKIES= '' # Your Twitter/X cookies, copy from broswer TWITTER_2FA_SECRET= # Two-factor authentication ``` ### 2. ÁºñËæëËßíËâ≤Êñá‰ª∂ - Ê†áÂáÜÁöÑËßíËâ≤‰∏™ÊÄßÂÆö‰πâÂú®Êñá‰ª∂ `characters/*.character.json`‰∏≠, ÊÇ®ÂèØ‰ª•‰øÆÊîπÂÆÉÊàñËÄÖÁõ¥Êé•‰ΩøÁî®ÂÆÉ„ÄÇ - ÊÇ®‰πüÂèØ‰ª•‰ΩøÁî® `node --loader ts-node/esm src/index.ts --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` Âä†ËΩΩËßíËâ≤Âπ∂ÂêåÊó∂ËøêË°åÂ§ö‰∏™Êú∫Âô®‰∫∫„ÄÇ - ÈúÄË¶ÅËØ¥ÊòéÁöÑÊòØ, Âú®`characters/*.character.json`‰∏≠, `clientsÂ≠óÊÆµÂØπÂ∫î**ÊúçÂä°**, ÈªòËÆ§ÂèØÈÄâ`"twitter", "discord", "telegram"`Á≠â, Â¶ÇÊûúÂú®`clients`‰∏≠Â°´ÂÖ•‰∫ÜÂ¶Ç"twitter"Á≠âÂÜÖÂÆπ, ÂàôÈúÄË¶ÅÂú® ‰∏äÈù¢ÁöÑ`env`ÈÖçÁΩÆÂØπÂ∫îÁöÑÁéØÂ¢ÉÂèòÈáè„ÄÇÂØπ`discord`Âíå`telegram`ÂêåÁêÜ„ÄÇ ``` { "name": "trump", "clients": ["twitter"], "modelProvider": "openai", ``` Âú®ÂÆåÊàêÁéØÂ¢ÉÂèòÈáèÂíåËßíËâ≤Êñá‰ª∂ÁöÑÈÖçÁΩÆÂêéÔºåËæìÂÖ•‰ª•‰∏ãÂëΩ‰ª§Ë°åÂêØÂä®‰Ω†ÁöÑbotÔºö ``` (A) ‰ΩøÁî®ÂêØÂä®Âô®(Starter) sh scripts/start.sh (B) ÊâãÂä®ÂêØÂä®Eliza pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start ``` # Ëá™ÂÆö‰πâEliza ### Ê∑ªÂä†Â∏∏ËßÑË°å‰∏∫ ‰∏∫ÈÅøÂÖçÂú®Ê†∏ÂøÉÁõÆÂΩï‰∏≠ÁöÑ Git ÂÜ≤Á™ÅÔºåÊàë‰ª¨Âª∫ËÆÆÂ∞ÜËá™ÂÆö‰πâÊìç‰ΩúÊ∑ªÂä†Âà∞ custom_actions ÁõÆÂΩï‰∏≠ÔºåÂπ∂Âú® elizaConfig.yaml Êñá‰ª∂‰∏≠ÈÖçÁΩÆËøô‰∫õÊìç‰Ωú„ÄÇÂèØ‰ª•ÂèÇËÄÉ elizaConfig.example.yaml Êñá‰ª∂‰∏≠ÁöÑÁ§∫‰æã„ÄÇ ## ÈÖçÁΩÆ‰∏çÂêåÁöÑÂ§ßÊ®°Âûã ÊÇ®ÂèØ‰ª•‰ΩøÁî®‰∏çÂêåÁöÑÂ§ßÊ®°ÂûãÊù•È©±Âä®ÊÇ®ÁöÑAI AgentÔºåÂàáÊç¢‰∏çÂêåÂ§ßÊ®°ÂûãÈúÄË¶Å‰∏§Ê≠•Ôºö 1. Á°ÆËÆ§ÊÇ®Âú®`.env`Êñá‰ª∂ÂÜÖÈÖçÁΩÆ‰∫ÜÂØπÂ∫îÁöÑÂ§ßÊ®°ÂûãAPI KeyÊàñÂØπÂ∫îÁöÑËÆøÈóÆÈÖçÁΩÆÔºå‰æãÂ¶ÇÂ¶ÇÊûúÊÇ®ÊÉ≥‰ΩøÁî®OpenAIÔºåÂàôÈúÄË¶ÅÊâæÂà∞`OPENAI_API_KEY`ÂèÇÊï∞ÔºåÂπ∂Â°´ÂÖ•ÊÇ®ÁöÑOpenAI API KeyÔºåÂπ∂‰ª•Ê≠§Á±ªÊé®„ÄÇ 2. Âú®ÊÇ®ÁöÑ*Character*Êñá‰ª∂ÈáåÊâæÂà∞`modelProvider`ÔºåÂπ∂Êõ¥ÊîπËøôÈáåÁöÑÂÜÖÂÆπÔºå‰æãÂ¶ÇÂ¶ÇÊûúÊÉ≥Ë¶ÅÂàáÊç¢Âà∞ClaudeÔºåÂàôÈúÄË¶ÅÂ°´ÂÖ•`anthropic`,‰ª•Ê≠§Êù•Ë°®ÊòéÊÇ®Â∞Ü‰ΩøÁî®anthropicÂ§ßÊ®°Âûã‰Ωú‰∏∫ÊÇ®ÁöÑÂØπÂ∫îAgentÁöÑProvider. Âú®`.env`Êñá‰ª∂ÂÜÖÊÇ®ÂèØ‰ª•ÊâæÂà∞‰∏çÂêåÂ§ßÊ®°ÂûãÁöÑËØ¶ÁªÜÈÖçÁΩÆÔºåÂåÖÊã¨ËÆæÂÆöÂÖ∑‰ΩìÊÉ≥Ë¶Å‰ΩøÁî®ÂØπÂ∫îÊèê‰æõÂïÜÁöÑÂì™‰∏™Ê®°ÂûãÔºå‰∏ãÊñπÊàë‰ª¨ÁªôÂá∫‰∫Ü‰∏§‰∏™ÂÆû‰æãÔºö ### ÈÖçÁΩÆOpenAI È¶ñÂÖàÊÇ®ÈúÄË¶ÅÂú®CharacterÊñá‰ª∂ÂÜÖÊåáÂÆömodel provider ```json "name": "C-3PO", "clients": [], "modelProvider": "openai" ... ``` ÂÖ∂Ê¨°ËØ∑Âú®`env`Êñá‰ª∂ÂÜÖÈÖçÁΩÆÁõ∏ÂÖ≥ÂèÇÊï∞ ``` # AI Model API Keys OPENAI_API_KEY= # OpenAI API key, starting with sk- SMALL_OPENAI_MODEL= # Default: gpt-4o-mini MEDIUM_OPENAI_MODEL= # Default: gpt-4o LARGE_OPENAI_MODEL= # Default: gpt-4o EMBEDDING_OPENAI_MODEL= # Default: text-embedding-3-small IMAGE_OPENAI_MODEL= # Default: dall-e-3 ``` ### ÈÖçÁΩÆAnthorpic ```json "name": "C-3PO", "clients": [], "modelProvider": "anthropic" ... ``` ÂÖ∂Ê¨°ËØ∑Âú®`env`Êñá‰ª∂ÂÜÖÈÖçÁΩÆÁõ∏ÂÖ≥ÂèÇÊï∞ ``` # Anthropic Configuration ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # For Claude SMALL_ANTHROPIC_MODEL= # Default: claude-3-haiku-20240307 MEDIUM_ANTHROPIC_MODEL= # Default: claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022 LARGE_ANTHROPIC_MODEL= # Default: claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022 ``` ## ÂÖ∂‰ªñË¶ÅÊ±Ç ÊÇ®ÂèØËÉΩÈúÄË¶ÅÂÆâË£Ö Sharp„ÄÇÂ¶ÇÊûúÂú®ÂêØÂä®Êó∂ÁúãÂà∞ÈîôËØØÔºåËØ∑Â∞ùËØï‰ΩøÁî®‰ª•‰∏ãÂëΩ‰ª§ÂÆâË£ÖÔºö ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` # ÁéØÂ¢ÉËÆæÁΩÆ ÊÇ®ÈúÄË¶ÅÂú® .env Êñá‰ª∂‰∏≠Ê∑ªÂä†ÁéØÂ¢ÉÂèòÈáè‰ª•ËøûÊé•Âà∞ÂêÑÁßçÂπ≥Âè∞Ôºö ``` # Required environment variables DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID= DISCORD_API_TOKEN= # Bot token OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-* # OpenAI API key, starting with sk- ELEVENLABS_XI_API_KEY= # API key from elevenlabs # ELEVENLABS SETTINGS ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_multilingual_v2 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STABILITY=0.5 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SIMILARITY_BOOST=0.9 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STYLE=0.66 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_USE_SPEAKER_BOOST=false ELEVENLABS_OPTIMIZE_STREAMING_LATENCY=4 ELEVENLABS_OUTPUT_FORMAT=pcm_16000 TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME= # Account username TWITTER_PASSWORD= # Account password TWITTER_EMAIL= # Account email X_SERVER_URL= XAI_API_KEY= XAI_MODEL= # For asking Claude stuff ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # EVM EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY # Solana SOLANA_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY SOLANA_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY # Fallback Wallet Configuration (deprecated) WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY BIRDEYE_API_KEY= SOL_ADDRESS=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112 SLIPPAGE=1 RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com HELIUS_API_KEY= ## Telegram TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN= TOGETHER_API_KEY= ``` # Êú¨Âú∞ËÆæÁΩÆ ### CUDAËÆæÁΩÆ Â¶ÇÊûú‰Ω†ÊúâÈ´òÊÄßËÉΩÁöÑËã±‰ºüËææÊòæÂç°Ôºå‰Ω†ÂèØ‰ª•‰ª•‰∏ãÂëΩ‰ª§Ë°åÈÄöËøáCUDAÊù•ÂÅöÊú¨Âú∞Âä†ÈÄü ``` pnpm install npx --no node-llama-cpp source download --gpu cuda ``` Á°Æ‰øù‰Ω†ÂÆâË£Ö‰∫ÜÂÆåÊï¥ÁöÑCUDAÂ∑•ÂÖ∑ÂåÖÔºåÂåÖÊã¨cuDNNÂíåcuBLAS ### Êú¨Âú∞ËøêË°å Ê∑ªÂä† XAI_MODEL Âπ∂Â∞ÜÂÖ∂ËÆæÁΩÆ‰∏∫‰∏äËø∞ [‰ΩøÁî® Llama ËøêË°å](#run-with-llama) ‰∏≠ÁöÑÈÄâÈ°π‰πã‰∏Ä ÊÇ®ÂèØ‰ª•Â∞Ü X_SERVER_URL Âíå XAI_API_KEY ÁïôÁ©∫ÔºåÂÆÉ‰ºö‰ªé huggingface ‰∏ãËΩΩÊ®°ÂûãÂπ∂Âú®Êú¨Âú∞Êü•ËØ¢ # ÂÆ¢Êà∑Á´Ø ÂÖ≥‰∫éÊÄé‰πàËÆæÁΩÆdiscord botÔºåÂèØ‰ª•Êü•ÁúãdiscordÁöÑÂÆòÊñπÊñáÊ°£ # ÂºÄÂèë ## ÊµãËØï Âá†ÁßçÊµãËØïÊñπÊ≥ïÁöÑÂëΩ‰ª§Ë°åÔºö ```bash pnpm test # Run tests once pnpm test:watch # Run tests in watch mode ``` ÂØπ‰∫éÊï∞ÊçÆÂ∫ìÁâπÂÆöÁöÑÊµãËØïÔºö ```bash pnpm test:sqlite # Run tests with SQLite pnpm test:sqljs # Run tests with SQL.js ``` ÊµãËØï‰ΩøÁî® Jest ÁºñÂÜôÔºå‰Ωç‰∫é src/\*_/_.test.ts Êñá‰ª∂‰∏≠„ÄÇÊµãËØïÁéØÂ¢ÉÈÖçÁΩÆÂ¶Ç‰∏ãÔºö - ‰ªé .env.test Âä†ËΩΩÁéØÂ¢ÉÂèòÈáè - ‰ΩøÁî® 2 ÂàÜÈíüÁöÑË∂ÖÊó∂Êó∂Èó¥Êù•ËøêË°åÈïøÊó∂Èó¥ËøêË°åÁöÑÊµãËØï - ÊîØÊåÅ ESM Ê®°Âùó - ÊåâÈ°∫Â∫èËøêË°åÊµãËØï (--runInBand) Ë¶ÅÂàõÂª∫Êñ∞ÊµãËØïÔºåËØ∑Âú®Ë¶ÅÊµãËØïÁöÑ‰ª£Á†ÅÊóÅËæπÊ∑ªÂä†‰∏Ä‰∏™ .test.ts Êñá‰ª∂„ÄÇ

files.content:
# Eliza ü§ñ
üìñ [Dokumentation](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/) | üéØ [Beispiele](https://github.com/thejoven/awesome-eliza)
## ‚ú® Funktionen - üõ†Ô∏è Voll ausgestattete Konnektoren f√ºr Discord, Twitter und Telegram - üë• Multi-Agenten- und Raumunterst√ºtzung - üìö Einfache Verarbeitung und Interaktion mit deinen Dokumenten - üíæ Abrufbarer Speicher und Dokumentenspeicher - üöÄ Hochgradig erweiterbar ‚Äì erstelle deine eigenen Aktionen und Clients - ‚òÅÔ∏è Unterst√ºtzt viele Modelle (lokales Llama, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq usw.) - üì¶ Einfach funktionsf√§hig! ## üéØ Anwendungsf√§lle - ü§ñ Chatbots - üïµÔ∏è Autonome Agenten - üìà Gesch√§ftsprozessmanagement - üéÆ NPCs in Videospielen - üß† Handel ## üöÄ Schnelleinstieg ### Voraussetzungen - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) > **Hinweis f√ºr Windows-Benutzer:** [WSL 2](https://learn.microsoft.com/de-de/windows/wsl/install-manual) ist erforderlich. ### Nutzung des Starters (Empfohlen) ```bash git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza-starter.git cp .env.example .env pnpm i && pnpm start ``` Lies dann die [Dokumentation](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/), um zu erfahren, wie du Eliza anpassen kannst. ### Manuelles Starten von Eliza (Nur empfohlen, wenn du genau wei√üt, was du tust) ```bash # Repository klonen git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza.git # Wechsle zur neuesten Version # Dieses Projekt entwickelt sich schnell weiter, daher empfehlen wir, die neueste Version zu verwenden git checkout $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0) ``` ### Eliza mit Gitpod starten [![In Gitpod √∂ffnen](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/#https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/tree/main) ### Bearbeite die .env-Datei Kopiere .env.example nach .env und f√ºlle die entsprechenden Werte aus. ``` cp .env.example .env ``` Hinweis: .env ist optional. Wenn du vorhast, mehrere unterschiedliche Agenten auszuf√ºhren, kannst du Geheimnisse √ºber die Charakter-JSON √ºbergeben. ### Eliza automatisch starten Dies f√ºhrt alle notwendigen Schritte aus, um das Projekt einzurichten und den Bot mit dem Standardcharakter zu starten. ```bash sh scripts/start.sh ``` ### Charakterdatei bearbeiten 1. √ñffne `agent/src/character.ts`, um den Standardcharakter zu bearbeiten. Kommentiere und bearbeite ihn. 2. Um benutzerdefinierte Charaktere zu laden: - Verwende `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` - Mehrere Charakterdateien k√∂nnen gleichzeitig geladen werden. 3. Verbinde mit X (Twitter) - √Ñndere `"clients": []` zu `"clients": ["twitter"]` in der Charakterdatei, um eine Verbindung mit X herzustellen. ### Eliza manuell starten ```bash pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start # Das Projekt entwickelt sich schnell weiter. Manchmal musst du das Projekt bereinigen, wenn du es nach einiger Zeit erneut aufrufst. pnpm clean ``` #### Zus√§tzliche Anforderungen M√∂glicherweise musst du Sharp installieren. Wenn beim Starten ein Fehler auftritt, versuche es mit folgendem Befehl: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` ### Community & Kontakt - [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/issues). Am besten geeignet f√ºr: Bugs, die du bei der Nutzung von Eliza findest, und Feature-Vorschl√§ge. - [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z). Am besten geeignet f√ºr: das Teilen deiner Anwendungen und den Austausch mit der Community. ## Contributors ## Star History [![Star History Chart](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=elizaos/eliza&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#elizaos/eliza&Date)

files.name: README_ES.md
files.content: # Eliza ## Funcionalidades - üõ† Conectores completos para Discord, Twitter y Telegram - üë• Soporte para m√∫ltiples agentes y salas - üìö Ingesti√≥n e interacci√≥n sencilla con documentos - üíæ Memoria recuperable y almacenamiento de documentos - üöÄ Altamente extensible - cree sus propias acciones y clientes para expandir capacidades - ‚òÅÔ∏è Soporta m√∫ltiples modelos, incluidos Llama local, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq y m√°s - üì¶ Funciona perfectamente ## Usos - ü§ñ Chatbots - üïµÔ∏è Agentes aut√≥nomos - üìà Gesti√≥n de procesos empresariales - üéÆ NPCs en videojuegos # Primeros Pasos **Requisitos (OBLIGATORIOS):** - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23.3+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) ### Edite el archivo .env - Copie el archivo .env.example a .env y complete los valores apropiados - Edite las variables de entorno de TWITTER para agregar nombre de usuario y contrase√±a del bot ### Edite el archivo de personaje - Revise el archivo `src/core/defaultCharacter.ts` - puede modificarlo - Tambi√©n puede cargar personajes con el comando `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` y ejecutar m√∫ltiples bots simult√°neamente. Despu√©s de configurar el archivo .env y el archivo de personaje, puede iniciar el bot con: ``` pnpm i pnpm start ``` # Personalizando a Eliza ### Agregando acciones personalizadas Para evitar conflictos en el directorio central, se recomienda agregar acciones personalizadas a un directorio `custom_actions` y luego agregarlas al archivo `elizaConfig.yaml`. Consulte el archivo `elizaConfig.example.yaml` para un ejemplo. ## Ejecuci√≥n con Diferentes Modelos ### Ejecutar con Llama Puede ejecutar modelos Llama 70B o 405B configurando la variable de ambiente `XAI_MODEL` en `meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct-Turbo` o `meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-405B-Instruct` ### Ejecutar con Grok Puede ejecutar modelos Grok configurando la variable de ambiente `XAI_MODEL` en `grok-beta` ### Ejecutar con OpenAI Puede ejecutar modelos OpenAI configurando la variable de ambiente `XAI_MODEL` en `gpt-4o-mini` o `gpt-4o` ## Requisitos Adicionales Puede ser necesario instalar Sharp. Si encuentra un error al iniciar, intente instalarlo con: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` # Configuraci√≥n del Entorno Deber√° agregar variables de ambiente a su archivo .env para conectarse a varias plataformas: ``` # Variables de ambiente obligatorias DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID= DISCORD_API_TOKEN= # Token del bot OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-* # Clave API de OpenAI, comenzando con sk- ELEVENLABS_XI_API_KEY= # Clave API de ElevenLabs GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY= # Clave API de Gemini # CONFIGURACIONES DE ELEVENLABS ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_multilingual_v2 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STABILITY=0.5 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SIMILARITY_BOOST=0.9 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STYLE=0.66 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_USE_SPEAKER_BOOST=false ELEVENLABS_OPTIMIZE_STREAMING_LATENCY=4 ELEVENLABS_OUTPUT_FORMAT=pcm_16000 TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME= # Nombre de usuario de la cuenta TWITTER_PASSWORD= # Contrase√±a de la cuenta TWITTER_EMAIL= # Correo electr√≥nico de la cuenta X_SERVER_URL= XAI_API_KEY= XAI_MODEL= # Para consultar a Claude ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # EVM EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY # Solana SOLANA_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY SOLANA_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY # Fallback Wallet Configuration (deprecated) WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY BIRDEYE_API_KEY= SOL_ADDRESS=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112 SLIPPAGE=1 RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com HELIUS_API_KEY= ## Telegram TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN= TOGETHER_API_KEY= ``` # Configuraci√≥n de Inferencia Local ### Configuraci√≥n CUDA Si tiene una GPU NVIDIA, puede instalar CUDA para acelerar significativamente la inferencia local. ``` pnpm install npx --no node-llama-cpp source download --gpu cuda ``` Aseg√∫rese de tener instalado el CUDA Toolkit, incluyendo cuDNN y cuBLAS. ### Ejecuci√≥n local Agregue XAI_MODEL y config√∫relo con una de las opciones de [Ejecutar con Llama](#ejecutar-con-llama) - puede dejar X_SERVER_URL y XAI_API_KEY en blanco, descargar√° el modelo de HuggingFace y realizar√° consultas localmente # Clientes ## Bot de Discord Para ayuda con la configuraci√≥n de su Bot de Discord, consulte: https://discordjs.guide/preparations/setting-up-a-bot-application.html # Desarrollo ## Pruebas Para ejecutar la suite de pruebas: ```bash pnpm test # Ejecutar pruebas una vez pnpm test:watch # Ejecutar pruebas en modo observaci√≥n ``` Para pruebas espec√≠ficas de base de datos: ```bash pnpm test:sqlite # Ejecutar pruebas con SQLite pnpm test:sqljs # Ejecutar pruebas con SQL.js ``` Las pruebas est√°n escritas con Jest y se pueden encontrar en archivos `src/**/*.test.ts`. El entorno de pruebas est√° configurado para: - Cargar variables de ambiente desde `.env.test` - Usar un l√≠mite de 2 minutos para pruebas de larga duraci√≥n - Soportar m√≥dulos ESM - Ejecutar pruebas en secuencia (--runInBand) Para crear nuevas pruebas, agregue un archivo `.test.ts` junto al c√≥digo que est√° probando.

## ‚ú® Caratteristiche - üõ†Ô∏è Connettori completi per Discord, Twitter e Telegram - üîó Supporto per tutti i modelli (Llama, Grok, OpenAI, Anthropic, ecc.) - üë• Supporto multi-agente e per stanze - üìö Acquisisci e interagisci facilmente con i tuoi documenti - üíæ Memoria recuperabile e archivio documenti - üöÄ Altamente estensibile - crea le tue azioni e clients personalizzati - ‚òÅÔ∏è Supporto di numerosi modelli (Llama locale, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq, ecc.) - üì¶ Funziona e basta! ## üéØ Casi d'uso - ü§ñ Chatbot - üïµÔ∏è Agenti Autonomi - üìà Gestione dei processi aziendali - üéÆ NPC per Videogiochi - üß† Trading ## üöÄ Avvio Rapido ### Prerequisiti - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) > **Nota per gli utenti Windows:** √à richiesto WSL ### Modifica il file .env Copia .env.example in .env e inserisci i valori appropriati ``` cp .env.example .env ``` ### Avvia Eliza Automaticamente Questo script eseguir√† tutti i comandi necessari per configurare il progetto e avviare il bot con il personaggio predefinito. ```bash sh scripts/start.sh ``` ### Modifica il file del personaggio 1. Apri `packages/agent/src/character.ts` per modificare il personaggio predefinito. Decommenta e modifica. 2. Per caricare personaggi personalizzati: - Usa `pnpm start --characters="percorso/del/tuo/personaggio.json"` - √à possibile caricare pi√π file di personaggi contemporaneamente ### Avvia Eliza Manualmente ```bash pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start # Il progetto evolve rapidamente; a volte √® necessario pulire il progetto se si ritorna sul progetto dopo un po' di tempo pnpm clean ``` #### Requisiti Aggiuntivi Potrebbe essere necessario installare Sharp. Se vedi un errore all'avvio, prova a installarlo con il seguente comando: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` ### Comunit√† e contatti - [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/issues). Ideale per segnalare bug riscontrati durante l‚Äôutilizzo di Eliza e proporre nuove funzionalit√†. - [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z). Ideale per condividere le tue applicazioni e interagire con la comunit√†. ## Contributori ## Cronologia Stelle [![Grafico Cronologia Stelle](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=elizaos/eliza&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#elizaos/eliza&Date)

files.content: # Eliza ## Ê©üËÉΩ - üõ† Discord„ÄÅTwitter„ÄÅTelegram„ÅÆ„Éï„É´Ê©üËÉΩ„Ç≥„Éç„ÇØ„Çø - üë• „Éû„É´„ÉÅ„Ç®„Éº„Ç∏„Çß„É≥„Éà„Åä„Çà„Å≥„É´„Éº„É†„Çµ„Éù„Éº„Éà - üìö „Éâ„Ç≠„É•„É°„É≥„Éà„ÅÆÁ∞°Âçò„Å™Âèñ„ÇäËæº„Åø„Å®ÂØæË©± - üíæ Ê§úÁ¥¢ÂèØËÉΩ„Å™„É°„É¢„É™„Åä„Çà„Å≥„Éâ„Ç≠„É•„É°„É≥„Éà„Çπ„Éà„Ç¢ - üöÄ È´ò„ÅÑÊã°ÂºµÊÄß - Ê©üËÉΩ„ÇíÊã°Âºµ„Åô„Çã„Åü„ÇÅ„ÅÆÁã¨Ëá™„ÅÆ„Ç¢„ÇØ„Ç∑„Éß„É≥„Å®„ÇØ„É©„Ç§„Ç¢„É≥„Éà„Çí‰ΩúÊàêÂèØËÉΩ - ‚òÅÔ∏è Llama„ÄÅOpenAI„ÄÅAnthropic„ÄÅGroq„Å™„Å©„ÄÅÂ§ö„Åè„ÅÆ„É¢„Éá„É´„Çí„Çµ„Éù„Éº„Éà - üì¶ „Åô„Åê„Å´‰Ωø„Åà„ÇãÔºÅ ## ‰Ωï„Å´‰Ωø„Åà„Çã„ÅÆ„ÅãÔºü - ü§ñ „ÉÅ„É£„ÉÉ„Éà„Éú„ÉÉ„Éà - üïµÔ∏è Ëá™Âæã„Ç®„Éº„Ç∏„Çß„É≥„Éà - üìà „Éì„Ç∏„Éç„Çπ„Éó„É≠„Çª„Çπ„ÅÆÂá¶ÁêÜ - üéÆ „Éì„Éá„Ç™„Ç≤„Éº„É†„ÅÆNPC # Âßã„ÇÅÊñπ **ÂøÖÈ†àÊù°‰ª∂:** - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) ### .env„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„ÅÆÁ∑®ÈõÜ - .env.example„Çí.env„Å´„Ç≥„Éî„Éº„Åó„ÄÅÈÅ©Âàá„Å™ÂÄ§„ÇíÂÖ•Âäõ - TWITTERÁí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞„ÇíÁ∑®ÈõÜ„Åó„Å¶„ÄÅ„Éú„ÉÉ„Éà„ÅÆ„É¶„Éº„Ç∂„ÉºÂêç„Å®„Éë„Çπ„ÉØ„Éº„Éâ„ÇíËøΩÂä† ### „Ç≠„É£„É©„ÇØ„Çø„Éº„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„ÅÆÁ∑®ÈõÜ - `src/core/defaultCharacter.ts`„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„ÇíÁ¢∫Ë™ç - „Åì„Çå„ÇíÂ§âÊõ¥ÂèØËÉΩ - `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"`„Çí‰ΩøÁî®„Åó„Å¶„Ç≠„É£„É©„ÇØ„Çø„Éº„Çí„É≠„Éº„Éâ„Åó„ÄÅË§áÊï∞„ÅÆ„Éú„ÉÉ„Éà„ÇíÂêåÊôÇ„Å´ÂÆüË°åÂèØËÉΩ .env„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„Å®„Ç≠„É£„É©„ÇØ„Çø„Éº„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„ÇíË®≠ÂÆö„Åó„ÅüÂæå„ÄÅ‰ª•‰∏ã„ÅÆ„Ç≥„Éû„É≥„Éâ„Åß„Éú„ÉÉ„Éà„ÇíËµ∑ÂãïÂèØËÉΩ: ``` pnpm i pnpm start ``` # Eliza„ÅÆ„Ç´„Çπ„Çø„Éû„Ç§„Ç∫ ### „Ç´„Çπ„Çø„É†„Ç¢„ÇØ„Ç∑„Éß„É≥„ÅÆËøΩÂä† „Ç≥„Ç¢„Éá„Ç£„É¨„ÇØ„Éà„É™„Åß„ÅÆGit„ÅÆÁ´∂Âêà„ÇíÈÅø„Åë„Çã„Åü„ÇÅ„Å´„ÄÅ„Ç´„Çπ„Çø„É†„Ç¢„ÇØ„Ç∑„Éß„É≥„Çí`custom_actions`„Éá„Ç£„É¨„ÇØ„Éà„É™„Å´ËøΩÂä†„Åó„ÄÅ„Åù„Çå„Çí`elizaConfig.yaml`„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„Å´ËøΩÂä†„Åô„Çã„Åì„Å®„Çí„ÅäÂãß„ÇÅ„Åó„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ‰æã„Å´„Å§„ÅÑ„Å¶„ÅØ`elizaConfig.example.yaml`„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„ÇíÂèÇÁÖß„Åó„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ„ÄÇ ## Áï∞„Å™„Çã„É¢„Éá„É´„Åß„ÅÆÂÆüË°å ### Llama„Åß„ÅÆÂÆüË°å `XAI_MODEL`Áí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞„Çí`meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct-Turbo`„Åæ„Åü„ÅØ`meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-405B-Instruct`„Å´Ë®≠ÂÆö„Åô„Çã„Åì„Å®„Åß„ÄÅLlama 70B„Åæ„Åü„ÅØ405B„É¢„Éá„É´„ÇíÂÆüË°åÂèØËÉΩ ### Grok„Åß„ÅÆÂÆüË°å `XAI_MODEL`Áí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞„Çí`grok-beta`„Å´Ë®≠ÂÆö„Åô„Çã„Åì„Å®„Åß„ÄÅGrok„É¢„Éá„É´„ÇíÂÆüË°åÂèØËÉΩ ### OpenAI„Åß„ÅÆÂÆüË°å `XAI_MODEL`Áí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞„Çí`gpt-4o-mini`„Åæ„Åü„ÅØ`gpt-4o`„Å´Ë®≠ÂÆö„Åô„Çã„Åì„Å®„Åß„ÄÅOpenAI„É¢„Éá„É´„ÇíÂÆüË°åÂèØËÉΩ ## ËøΩÂä†„ÅÆË¶Å‰ª∂ Sharp„Çí„Ç§„É≥„Çπ„Éà„Éº„É´„Åô„ÇãÂøÖË¶Å„Åå„ÅÇ„Çã„Åã„ÇÇ„Åó„Çå„Åæ„Åõ„Çì„ÄÇËµ∑ÂãïÊôÇ„Å´„Ç®„É©„Éº„ÅåË°®Á§∫„Åï„Çå„ÅüÂ†¥Âêà„ÅØ„ÄÅ‰ª•‰∏ã„ÅÆ„Ç≥„Éû„É≥„Éâ„Åß„Ç§„É≥„Çπ„Éà„Éº„É´„ÇíË©¶„Åø„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` # Áí∞Â¢ÉË®≠ÂÆö ÔøΩÔøΩÔøΩ„Åæ„Åñ„Åæ„Å™„Éó„É©„ÉÉ„Éà„Éï„Ç©„Éº„É†„Å´Êé•Á∂ö„Åô„Çã„Åü„ÇÅ„Å´„ÄÅ.env„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„Å´Áí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞„ÇíËøΩÂä†„Åô„ÇãÂøÖË¶Å„Åå„ÅÇ„Çä„Åæ„Åô: ``` # ÂøÖÈ†àÁí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞ DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID= DISCORD_API_TOKEN= # „Éú„ÉÉ„Éà„Éà„Éº„ÇØ„É≥ OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-* # OpenAI API„Ç≠„Éº„ÄÅsk-„ÅßÂßã„Åæ„Çã ELEVENLABS_XI_API_KEY= # elevenlabs„Åã„Çâ„ÅÆAPI„Ç≠„Éº # ELEVENLABSË®≠ÂÆö ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_multilingual_v2 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STABILITY=0.5 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SIMILARITY_BOOST=0.9 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STYLE=0.66 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_USE_SPEAKER_BOOST=false ELEVENLABS_OPTIMIZE_STREAMING_LATENCY=4 ELEVENLABS_OUTPUT_FORMAT=pcm_16000 TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME= # „Ç¢„Ç´„Ç¶„É≥„Éà„ÅÆ„É¶„Éº„Ç∂„ÉºÂêç TWITTER_PASSWORD= # „Ç¢„Ç´„Ç¶„É≥„Éà„ÅÆ„Éë„Çπ„ÉØ„Éº„Éâ TWITTER_EMAIL= # „Ç¢„Ç´„Ç¶„É≥„Éà„ÅÆ„É°„Éº„É´ X_SERVER_URL= XAI_API_KEY= XAI_MODEL= # Claude„Å´Ë≥™Âïè„Åô„Çã„Åü„ÇÅ ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # EVM EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY # Solana SOLANA_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY SOLANA_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY # Fallback Wallet Configuration (deprecated) WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY BIRDEYE_API_KEY= SOL_ADDRESS=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112 SLIPPAGE=1 RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com HELIUS_API_KEY= ## Telegram TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN= TOGETHER_API_KEY= ``` # „É≠„Éº„Ç´„É´Êé®Ë´ñË®≠ÂÆö ### CUDAË®≠ÂÆö NVIDIA GPU„ÇíÊåÅ„Å£„Å¶„ÅÑ„ÇãÂ†¥Âêà„ÄÅCUDA„Çí„Ç§„É≥„Çπ„Éà„Éº„É´„Åó„Å¶„É≠„Éº„Ç´„É´Êé®Ë´ñ„ÇíÂ§ßÂπÖ„Å´È´òÈÄüÂåñÂèØËÉΩ ``` pnpm install npx --no node-llama-cpp source download --gpu cuda ``` CUDA Toolkit„ÄÅcuDNN„ÄÅcuBLAS„Çí„Ç§„É≥„Çπ„Éà„Éº„É´„Åó„Å¶„ÅÑ„Çã„Åì„Å®„ÇíÁ¢∫Ë™ç„Åó„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ„ÄÇ ### „É≠„Éº„Ç´„É´„Åß„ÅÆÂÆüË°å XAI_MODEL„ÇíËøΩÂä†„Åó„ÄÅ[Llama„Åß„ÅÆÂÆüË°å](#run-with-llama)„ÅÆ„Ç™„Éó„Ç∑„Éß„É≥„ÅÆ„ÅÑ„Åö„Çå„Åã„Å´Ë®≠ÂÆö - X_SERVER_URL„Å®XAI_API_KEY„ÇíÁ©∫ÁôΩ„ÅÆ„Åæ„Åæ„Å´„Åó„Å¶„Åä„Åè„Å®„ÄÅhuggingface„Åã„Çâ„É¢„Éá„É´„Çí„ÉÄ„Ç¶„É≥„É≠„Éº„Éâ„Åó„ÄÅ„É≠„Éº„Ç´„É´„Åß„ÇØ„Ç®„É™„ÇíÂÆüË°å„Åó„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ # „ÇØ„É©„Ç§„Ç¢„É≥„Éà ## Discord„Éú„ÉÉ„Éà Discord„Éú„ÉÉ„Éà„ÅÆË®≠ÂÆö„Å´Èñ¢„Åô„Çã„Éò„É´„Éó„Å´„Å§„ÅÑ„Å¶„ÅØ„ÄÅ„Åì„Å°„Çâ„ÇíÂèÇÁÖß„Åó„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ: https://discordjs.guide/preparations/setting-up-a-bot-application.html # ÈñãÁô∫ ## „ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà „ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„Çπ„Ç§„Éº„Éà„ÇíÂÆüË°å„Åô„Çã„Å´„ÅØ: ```bash pnpm test # „ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„Çí‰∏ÄÂ∫¶ÂÆüË°å pnpm test:watch # „Ç¶„Ç©„ÉÉ„ÉÅ„É¢„Éº„Éâ„Åß„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÇíÂÆüË°å ``` „Éá„Éº„Çø„Éô„Éº„ÇπÂõ∫Êúâ„ÅÆ„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÅÆÂ†¥Âêà: ```bash pnpm test:sqlite # SQLite„Åß„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÇíÂÆüË°å pnpm test:sqljs # SQL.js„Åß„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÇíÂÆüË°å ``` „ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÅØJest„Çí‰ΩøÁî®„Åó„Å¶Ë®òËø∞„Åï„Çå„Å¶„Åä„Çä„ÄÅ`src/**/*.test.ts`„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„Å´„ÅÇ„Çä„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ„ÉÜ„Çπ„ÉàÁí∞Â¢É„ÅØÊ¨°„ÅÆ„Çà„ÅÜ„Å´ÊßãÊàê„Åï„Çå„Å¶„ÅÑ„Åæ„Åô: - `.env.test`„Åã„ÇâÁí∞Â¢ÉÂ§âÊï∞„Çí„É≠„Éº„Éâ - Èï∑ÊôÇÈñìÂÆüË°å„Åï„Çå„Çã„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÅÆ„Åü„ÇÅ„Å´2ÂàÜ„ÅÆ„Çø„Ç§„É†„Ç¢„Ç¶„Éà„Çí‰ΩøÁî® - ESM„É¢„Ç∏„É•„Éº„É´„Çí„Çµ„Éù„Éº„Éà - „ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„ÇíÈ†ÜÁï™„Å´ÂÆüË°å (--runInBand) Êñ∞„Åó„ÅÑ„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„Çí‰ΩúÊàê„Åô„Çã„Å´„ÅØ„ÄÅ„ÉÜ„Çπ„Éà„Åô„Çã„Ç≥„Éº„Éâ„ÅÆÈö£„Å´`.test.ts`„Éï„Ç°„Ç§„É´„ÇíËøΩÂä†„Åó„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ

files.content:
# Eliza ü§ñ
üìñ [Dokumentacja](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/) | üéØ [Przyk≈Çady](https://github.com/thejoven/awesome-eliza)
## ‚ú® Cechy modelu: - üõ†Ô∏è Pe≈Çne wsparcie dla Discorda, Telegrama i Twittera - üîó Wsparcie dla wszystkich modeli AI (Llama, Grok, OpenAI, Anthropic, itd.) - üë• Wiele osobowo≈õci jednocze≈õnie oraz wsparcie dla pokoi - üìö Prosta konstrukcja i ≈Çatwo≈õƒá modyfikacji ustawie≈Ñ - üíæ Przywracalna pamiƒôƒá i opcja przechowywania dokument√≥w - üöÄ Wiele mo≈ºliwo≈õci rozszerze≈Ñ - tw√≥rz w≈Çasne klienty, aplikacje itd - ‚òÅÔ∏è Wsparcie dla szerokiej gamy modeli (local Llama, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq, etc.) - üì¶ To po prostu dzia≈Ça! ## Poradniki wideo [AI Agent Dev School](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ArptLpQiKfI&list=PLx5pnFXdPTRzWla0RaOxALTSTnVq53fKL) ## üéØ Przyk≈Çady zastosowania - ü§ñ Chatboty - üïµÔ∏è Autonomiczni Agenci - üìà Utrzymanie proces√≥w biznesowych - üéÆ Zaplecze dla postaci NPC w grach - üß† Handel ## üöÄ Jak zaczƒÖƒá? ### Wstƒôpne wymagania: - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) > **Notka dla u≈ºytkownik√≥w Windowsa:** [WSL 2](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-manual) jest wymagane!. ### U≈ºycie startera (Rekomendowane) ```bash git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza-starter.git cd eliza-starter cp .env.example .env pnpm i && pnpm build && pnpm start ``` Gdy agent siƒô uruchomi, powinien pojawiƒá siƒô komunikat aby uruchomiƒá komendƒô "pnpm start:client". Wtedy trzeba odpaliƒá drugi terminal, przej≈õƒá do tego samego folderu, w kt√≥rym mamy sklonowany kod z Githuba i odpaliƒá tƒÖ komendƒô, aby byƒá w stanie rozpoczƒÖƒá konwersacjƒô z naszym botem. ```bash pnpm start:client ``` Nastƒôpnie zapoznaj siƒô z [DokumentacjƒÖ](https://elizaos.github.io/eliza/). Tam jest szceg√≥≈Çowo opisane, jak modyfikowaƒá i dopasowaƒá Elizƒô do w≈Çasnych potrzeb. ### Manualny start (Przeznaczone dla os√≥b, kt√≥re wiedzƒÖ, co robiƒÖ) ```bash # Sklonuj repozytorium git clone https://github.com/elizaos/eliza.git # Sprawd≈∫, czy na pewno masz najnowszƒÖ wersjƒô # Projekt rozrasta siƒô bardzo szybko, dlatego zalecane jest aby czƒôsto sprawdzaƒá wersjƒô git checkout $(git describe --tags --abbrev=0) ``` ### Start przy u≈ºyciu Gitpod'a [![Otw√≥rz w Gitpodzie](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/#https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/tree/main) ### Edytuj plik .env Zmie≈Ñ nazwƒô pliku .env.example na .env i wype≈Çnij warto≈õci zmiennych, kt√≥re bƒôdƒÖ potrzebne do uruchomienia aplikacji. ``` cp .env.example .env ``` Uwaga: .env jest opcjonalne. Je≈ºeli planujesz stawiaƒá wiƒôcej ni≈º jednƒÖ postaƒá, zalecane jest korzystanie z plik√≥w JSON dedykowanych dla charakter√≥w. Bƒôdzie to bardziej przejrzyste i ≈Çatwiejsze do znalezienia gdy trzeba bƒôdzie wprowadziƒá jakie≈õ zmiany. ### Automatyczny start Elizy Ta komenda postawi projekt i uruchomi bota z domy≈õlnym charakterem. ```bash sh scripts/start.sh ``` ### Edycja pliku postaci 1. Otw√≥rz `packages/core/src/defaultCharacter.ts` aby zmodyfikowaƒá postaƒá. Odkomentuj i edytuj. 2. Aby za≈Çadowaƒá niestandardowe osobowo≈õci: - Uzyj komendy `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` - Wiele plik√≥w z osobowo≈õciami mo≈ºe byƒá za≈Çadowana jednocze≈õnie 3. Po≈ÇƒÖcz z platformƒÖ X (niegdy≈õ Twitter) - zamie≈Ñ `"clients": []` na `"clients": ["twitter"]` w pliku osobowo≈õci aby po≈ÇƒÖczyƒá z X ### Manualny Start Elizy ```bash pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start # Projekt rozwija siƒô bardzo szybko, dlatego je≈ºeli robisz sobie przerwƒô na jaki≈õ czas i wejdzie w miƒôdzyczasie du≈ºo zmian, dobrze jest u≈ºyƒá tej komendy: pnpm clean ``` #### Dodatkowe wymagania Mo≈ºesz musieƒá zainstalowaƒá pakiet Sharp. Je≈ºeli przy odpalaniu projektu wyskakuje b≈ÇƒÖd, spr√≥buj go zainstalowaƒá tƒÖ komendƒÖ: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` ### Spo≈Çeczno≈õƒá i kontakt - [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/issues). Korzystaj w przypadku gdy napotkasz na jakie≈õ bugi podczas uzywania Elizy, lub masz jakie≈õ propozycje rozwoju. - [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z). U≈ºywaj, gdy chcesz siƒô pochwaliƒá swojƒÖ aplikacjƒÖ lub po prostu pogadaƒá z kim≈õ. ## Osoby zaanga≈ºowane w rozw√≥j: ## Historia gwiazdek [![Wykres historii gwiazdek](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=elizaos/eliza&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#elizaos/eliza&Date)

files.name: README_PTBR.md
files.content: # Eliza ## Funcionalidades - üõ† Conectores completos para Discord, Twitter e Telegram - üë• Suporte a m√∫ltiplos agentes e salas - üìö Ingest√£o e intera√ß√£o f√°cil com seus documentos - üíæ Mem√≥ria recuper√°vel e armazenamento de documentos - üöÄ Altamente extens√≠vel - crie suas pr√≥prias a√ß√µes e clientes para estender as capacidades - ‚òÅÔ∏è Suporta muitos modelos, incluindo Llama local, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq e mais - üì¶ Funciona perfeitamente! ## Para que posso us√°-lo? - ü§ñ Chatbots - üïµÔ∏è Agentes aut√¥nomos - üìà Gest√£o de processos empresariais - üéÆ NPCs em jogos de v√≠deo # Come√ßando **Pr√©-requisitos (OBRIGAT√ìRIO):** - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23.3+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) ### Edite o arquivo .env - Copie .env.example para .env e preencha os valores apropriados - Edite as vari√°veis de ambiente do TWITTER para adicionar o nome de usu√°rio e senha do seu bot ### Edite o arquivo de personagem - Confira o arquivo `src/core/defaultCharacter.ts` - voc√™ pode modific√°-lo - Voc√™ tamb√©m pode carregar personagens com o comando `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` e executar m√∫ltiplos bots ao mesmo tempo. Ap√≥s configurar o arquivo .env e o arquivo de personagem, voc√™ pode iniciar o bot com o seguinte comando: ``` pnpm i pnpm start ``` # Personalizando Eliza ### Adicionando a√ß√µes personalizadas Para evitar conflitos no diret√≥rio core, recomendamos adicionar a√ß√µes personalizadas a um diret√≥rio `custom_actions` e depois adicion√°-las ao arquivo `elizaConfig.yaml`. Veja o arquivo `elizaConfig.example.yaml` para um exemplo. ## Executando com diferentes modelos ### Executar com Llama Voc√™ pode executar modelos Llama 70B ou 405B configurando a vari√°vel de ambiente `XAI_MODEL` para `meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct-Turbo` ou `meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-405B-Instruct` ### Executar com Grok Voc√™ pode executar modelos Grok configurando a vari√°vel de ambiente `XAI_MODEL` para `grok-beta` ### Executar com OpenAI Voc√™ pode executar modelos OpenAI configurando a vari√°vel de ambiente `XAI_MODEL` para `gpt-4o-mini` ou `gpt-4o` ## Requisitos Adicionais Pode ser necess√°rio instalar o Sharp. Se voc√™ encontrar um erro ao iniciar, tente instal√°-lo com o seguinte comando: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` # Configura√ß√£o do Ambiente Voc√™ precisar√° adicionar vari√°veis de ambiente ao seu arquivo .env para se conectar a v√°rias plataformas: ``` # Vari√°veis de ambiente obrigat√≥rias DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID= DISCORD_API_TOKEN= # Token do bot OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-* # Chave API do OpenAI, come√ßando com sk- ELEVENLABS_XI_API_KEY= # Chave API do elevenlabs GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY= # Chave API do Gemini # CONFIGURA√á√ïES DO ELEVENLABS ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_multilingual_v2 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STABILITY=0.5 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SIMILARITY_BOOST=0.9 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STYLE=0.66 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_USE_SPEAKER_BOOST=false ELEVENLABS_OPTIMIZE_STREAMING_LATENCY=4 ELEVENLABS_OUTPUT_FORMAT=pcm_16000 TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME= # Nome de usu√°rio da conta TWITTER_PASSWORD= # Senha da conta TWITTER_EMAIL= # Email da conta X_SERVER_URL= XAI_API_KEY= XAI_MODEL= # Para perguntar coisas ao Claude ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # EVM EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY # Solana SOLANA_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY SOLANA_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY # Fallback Wallet Configuration (deprecated) WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY BIRDEYE_API_KEY= SOL_ADDRESS=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112 SLIPPAGE=1 RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com HELIUS_API_KEY= ## Telegram TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN= TOGETHER_API_KEY= ``` # Configura√ß√£o de Infer√™ncia Local ### Configura√ß√£o CUDA Se voc√™ tiver uma GPU NVIDIA, pode instalar o CUDA para acelerar dramaticamente a infer√™ncia local. ``` pnpm install npx --no node-llama-cpp source download --gpu cuda ``` Certifique-se de ter instalado o CUDA Toolkit, incluindo cuDNN e cuBLAS. ### Executando localmente Adicione XAI_MODEL e configure-o para uma das op√ß√µes acima de [Executar com Llama](#executar-com-llama) - voc√™ pode deixar X_SERVER_URL e XAI_API_KEY em branco, ele baixa o modelo do huggingface e faz consultas localmente # Clientes ## Bot do Discord Para ajuda com a configura√ß√£o do seu Bot do Discord, confira aqui: https://discordjs.guide/preparations/setting-up-a-bot-application.html # Desenvolvimento ## Testes Para executar a su√≠te de testes: ```bash pnpm test # Executar testes uma vez pnpm test:watch # Executar testes no modo watch ``` Para testes espec√≠ficos de banco de dados: ```bash pnpm test:sqlite # Executar testes com SQLite pnpm test:sqljs # Executar testes com SQL.js ``` Os testes s√£o escritos usando Jest e podem ser encontrados em arquivos `src/**/*.test.ts`. O ambiente de teste est√° configurado para: - Carregar vari√°veis de ambiente de `.env.test` - Usar um tempo limite de 2 minutos para testes de longa dura√ß√£o - Suportar m√≥dulos ESM - Executar testes em sequ√™ncia (--runInBand) Para criar novos testes, adicione um arquivo `.test.ts` adjacente ao c√≥digo que voc√™ est√° testando.

files.content: # Eliza ## Funkcionalnosti - üõ† Kompletni konektori za Discord, Twitter i Telegram - üë• Podr≈°ka za vi≈°e agenata i soba - üìö Jednostavna ingestija i interakcija sa dokumentima - üíæ Memorija koja se mo≈æe povratiti i skladi≈°tenje dokumenata - üöÄ Visoko pro≈°irivo - kreirajte sopstvene akcije i klijente za pro≈°irenje moguƒánosti - ‚òÅÔ∏è Podr≈æava vi≈°e modela, ukljuƒçujuƒái Llama lokalno, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq i vi≈°e - üì¶ Radi besprekorno ## Upotrebe - ü§ñ Chatbotovi - üïµÔ∏è Autonomni agenti - üìà Upravljanje poslovnim procesima - üéÆ NPC-ovi u video igrama # Prvi Koraci **Zahtevi (OBAVEZNI):** - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23.3+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) ### Uredite .env datoteku - Kopirajte datoteku .env.example u .env i popunite odgovarajuƒáe vrednosti - Uredite TWITTER promenljive okru≈æenja da dodate korisniƒçko ime i lozinku bota ### Uredite datoteku karaktera - Pregledajte datoteku `src/core/defaultCharacter.ts` - mo≈æete je modifikovati - Takoƒëe mo≈æete uƒçitati karaktere sa komandom `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` i pokrenuti vi≈°e botova istovremeno. Nakon ≈°to konfiguri≈°ete .env datoteku i datoteku karaktera, mo≈æete pokrenuti bota sa: ``` pnpm i pnpm start ``` # Personalizacija Elize ### Dodavanje prilagoƒëenih akcija Da biste izbegli sukobe u centralnom direktorijumu, preporuƒçuje se dodavanje prilagoƒëenih akcija u direktorijum `custom_actions` i zatim ih dodajte u datoteku `elizaConfig.yaml`. Pogledajte datoteku `elizaConfig.example.yaml` za primer. ## Pokretanje sa Razliƒçitim Modelima ### Pokretanje sa Llama Mo≈æete pokrenuti Llama modele 70B ili 405B pode≈°avanjem promenljive okru≈æenja `XAI_MODEL` na `meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct-Turbo` ili `meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-405B-Instruct` ### Pokretanje sa Grok Mo≈æete pokrenuti Grok modele pode≈°avanjem promenljive okru≈æenja `XAI_MODEL` na `grok-beta` ### Pokretanje sa OpenAI Mo≈æete pokrenuti OpenAI modele pode≈°avanjem promenljive okru≈æenja `XAI_MODEL` na `gpt-4o-mini` ili `gpt-4o` ## Dodatni Zahtevi Mo≈æda ƒáe biti potrebno instalirati Sharp. Ako naiƒëete na gre≈°ku prilikom pokretanja, poku≈°ajte da ga instalirate sa: ``` pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` # Konfiguracija Okru≈æenja Trebaƒáe vam da dodate promenljive okru≈æenja u va≈°u .env datoteku da biste se povezali sa razliƒçitim platformama: ``` # Obavezne promenljive okru≈æenja DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID= DISCORD_API_TOKEN= # Token bota OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-* # API kljuƒç OpenAI, poƒçinje sa sk- ELEVENLABS_XI_API_KEY= # API kljuƒç ElevenLabs GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY= # API kljuƒç Gemini # KONFIGURACIJE ELEVENLABS ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_multilingual_v2 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STABILITY=0.5 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SIMILARITY_BOOST=0.9 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STYLE=0.66 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_USE_SPEAKER_BOOST=false ELEVENLABS_OPTIMIZE_STREAMING_LATENCY=4 ELEVENLABS_OUTPUT_FORMAT=pcm_16000 TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME= # Korisniƒçko ime naloga TWITTER_PASSWORD= # Lozinka naloga TWITTER_EMAIL= # Email naloga X_SERVER_URL= XAI_API_KEY= XAI_MODEL= # Za konsultacije sa Claude ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # EVM EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY # Solana SOLANA_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY SOLANA_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY # Konfiguracija rezervnog novƒçanika (zastarelo) WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY BIRDEYE_API_KEY= SOL_ADDRESS=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112 SLIPPAGE=1 RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com HELIUS_API_KEY= ## Telegram TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN= TOGETHER_API_KEY= ``` # Konfiguracija Lokalne Inference ### Konfiguracija CUDA Ako imate NVIDIA GPU, mo≈æete instalirati CUDA da znaƒçajno ubrzate lokalnu inferencu. ``` pnpm install npx --no node-llama-cpp source download --gpu cuda ``` Uverite se da imate instaliran CUDA Toolkit, ukljuƒçujuƒái cuDNN i cuBLAS. ### Lokalno Pokretanje Dodajte XAI_MODEL i konfiguri≈°ite ga sa jednom od opcija iz [Pokretanje sa Llama](#pokretanje-sa-llama) - mo≈æete ostaviti X_SERVER_URL i XAI_API_KEY praznim, preuzeƒáe model sa HuggingFace i izvr≈°iti upite lokalno # Klijenti ## Discord Bot Za pomoƒá sa konfiguracijom va≈°eg Discord Bota, pogledajte: https://discordjs.guide/preparations/setting-up-a-bot-application.html # Razvoj ## Testiranje Za pokretanje test suite-a: ```bash pnpm test # Pokreni testove jednom pnpm test:watch # Pokreni testove u re≈æimu posmatranja ``` Za specifiƒçne testove baze podataka: ```bash pnpm test:sqlite # Pokreni testove sa SQLite pnpm test:sqljs # Pokreni testove sa SQL.js ``` Testovi su napisani sa Jest i mogu se naƒái u datotekama `src/**/*.test.ts`. Testno okru≈æenje je konfigurisano za: - Uƒçitavanje promenljivih okru≈æenja iz `.env.test` - Kori≈°ƒáenje limita od 2 minuta za dugotrajne testove - Podr≈°ku za ESM module - Pokretanje testova u sekvenci (--runInBand) Za kreiranje novih testova, dodajte `.test.ts` datoteku pored koda koji testirate.

## ‚ú® –û—Å–æ–±–µ–Ω–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏ - üõ† –ü–æ–ª–Ω–æ—Ü–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –∫–æ–Ω–Ω–µ–∫—Ç–æ—Ä—ã –¥–ª—è Discord, Twitter –∏ Telegram - üë• –ü–æ–¥–¥–µ—Ä–∂–∫–∞ –Ω–µ—Å–∫–æ–ª—å–∫–∏—Ö –∞–≥–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤ –∏ –∫–æ–º–Ω–∞—Ç - üìö –ü—Ä–æ—Å—Ç–æ–µ –¥–æ–±–∞–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ –∏ –≤–∑–∞–∏–º–æ–¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏–µ —Å –≤–∞—à–∏–º–∏ –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–∞–º–∏ - üíæ –ó–∞–ø–æ–º–∏–Ω–∞–Ω–∏–µ –∫–æ–Ω—Ç–µ–∫—Ç–∞ –∏ —Ö—Ä–∞–Ω–∏–ª–∏—â–µ –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤ - üöÄ –í—ã—Å–æ–∫–∞—è –º–∞—à—Ç–∞–±–∏—Ä—É–µ–º–æ—Å—Ç—å - —Å–æ–∑–¥–∞–≤–∞–π—Ç–µ —Å–≤–æ–∏ —Å–æ–±—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏—è –∏ –∫–ª–∏–µ–Ω—Ç—ã –¥–ª—è —Ä–∞—Å—à–∏—Ä–µ–Ω–∏—è –≤–æ–∑–º–æ–∂–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–µ–π - ‚òÅÔ∏è –ü–æ–¥–¥–µ—Ä–∂–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç –º–Ω–æ–∂–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ –º–æ–¥–µ–ª–µ–π, –≤–∫–ª—é—á–∞—è –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã–µ Llama, OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq –∏ –¥—Ä—É–≥–∏–µ - üì¶ –ü—Ä–æ—Å—Ç–æ—Ç–∞ –≤ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–µ! ## üéØ –î–ª—è —á–µ–≥–æ —ç—Ç–æ –º–æ–∂–Ω–æ –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å? - ü§ñ –ß–∞—Ç-–±–æ—Ç—ã - üïµÔ∏è –ê–≤—Ç–æ–Ω–æ–º–Ω—ã–µ –∞–≥–µ–Ω—Ç—ã - üìà –û–±—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∫–∞ –±–∏–∑–Ω–µ—Å-–ø—Ä–æ—Ü–µ—Å—Å–æ–≤ - üéÆ NPC –≤ –≤–∏–¥–µ–æ–∏–≥—Ä–∞—Ö - üß† –¢–æ—Ä–≥–æ–≤–ª—è ## üåç –ü–µ—Ä–µ–≤–æ–¥—ã
–î–æ—Å—Ç—É–ø–Ω—ã–µ —è–∑—ã–∫–∏ - [‰∏≠ÊñáËØ¥Êòé](./README_CN.md) - [Êó•Êú¨Ë™û„ÅÆË™¨Êòé](./README_JA.md) - [ÌïúÍµ≠Ïñ¥ ÏÑ§Î™Ö](./README_KOR.md) - [Instructions en fran√ßais](./README_FR.md) - [Instru√ß√µes em portugu√™s](./README_PTBR.md) - [–ò–Ω—Å—Ç—Ä—É–∫—Ü–∏—è –Ω–∞ —Ä—É—Å—Å–∫–æ–º](./README_RU.md)

# üöÄ–ù–∞—á–∞–ª–æ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—ã **–ù–µ–æ–±—Ö–æ–¥–∏–º—ã–µ —É—Å–ª–æ–≤–∏—è (–û–ë–Ø–ó–ê–¢–ï–õ–¨–ù–û):** - [Python 2.7+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) - [Node.js 23.3+](https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm) - [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/installation) > **–î–ª—è Windows –ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞—Ç–µ–ª–µ–π:** —Ç—Ä–µ–±—É–µ—Ç—Å—è WSL ### –†–µ–¥–∞–∫—Ç–∏—Ä–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞ .env - –°–∫–æ–ø–∏—Ä—É–π—Ç–µ `.env.example` –≤ `.env` –∏ –∑–∞–ø–æ–ª–Ω–∏—Ç–µ —Å–æ–æ—Ç–≤–µ—Ç—Å—Ç–≤—É—é—â–∏–º–∏ –∑–Ω–∞—á–µ–Ω–∏—è–º–∏ ```bash cp .env.example .env ``` ### –†–µ–¥–∞–∫—Ç–∏—Ä–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞ –ø–µ—Ä—Å–æ–Ω–∞–∂–∞ 1. –û—Ç–∫—Ä–æ–π—Ç–µ `src/core/defaultCharacter.ts`, —á—Ç–æ–±—ã –∏–∑–º–µ–Ω–∏—Ç—å –ø–µ—Ä—Å–æ–Ω–∞–∂–∞ –ø–æ —É–º–æ–ª—á–∞–Ω–∏—é. 2. –î–ª—è –∑–∞–≥—Ä—É–∑–∫–∏ –ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å—Å–∫–∏—Ö –ø–µ—Ä—Å–æ–Ω–∞–∂–µ–π: - –ò—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑—É–π—Ç–µ –∫–æ–º–∞–Ω–¥—É `pnpm start --characters="path/to/your/character.json"` - –ú–æ–∂–Ω–æ –∑–∞–≥—Ä—É–∂–∞—Ç—å –Ω–µ—Å–∫–æ–ª—å–∫–æ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–æ–≤ –ø–µ—Ä—Å–æ–Ω–∞–∂–µ–π –æ–¥–Ω–æ–≤—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω–æ. ### –ó–∞–ø—É—Å–∫ Eliza –ü–æ—Å–ª–µ –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∏ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞ `.env` –∏ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞ –ø–µ—Ä—Å–æ–Ω–∞–∂–∞ –≤—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ –∑–∞–ø—É—Å—Ç–∏—Ç—å –±–æ—Ç–∞ —Å –ø–æ–º–æ—â—å—é —Å–ª–µ–¥—É—é—â–µ–π –∫–æ–º–∞–Ω–¥—ã: ```bash pnpm i pnpm build pnpm start # –ü—Ä–æ–µ–∫—Ç –±—ã—Å—Ç—Ä–æ —Ä–∞–∑–≤–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è, –∏–Ω–æ–≥–¥–∞ –Ω—É–∂–Ω–æ –æ—á–∏—â–∞—Ç—å –ø—Ä–æ–µ–∫—Ç, –µ—Å–ª–∏ –≤—ã –≤–æ–∑–≤—Ä–∞—â–∞–µ—Ç–µ—Å—å –∫ –Ω–µ–º—É —Å–ø—É—Å—Ç—è –≤—Ä–µ–º—è pnpm clean ``` #### –î–æ–ø–æ–ª–Ω–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã–µ —Ç—Ä–µ–±–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è –í–æ–∑–º–æ–∂–Ω–æ, –ø–æ—Ç—Ä–µ–±—É–µ—Ç—Å—è —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏—Ç—å Sharp. –ï—Å–ª–∏ –ø—Ä–∏ –∑–∞–ø—É—Å–∫–µ –≤–æ–∑–Ω–∏–∫–Ω–µ—Ç –æ—à–∏–±–∫–∞, –ø–æ–ø—Ä–æ–±—É–π—Ç–µ —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏—Ç—å –µ–≥–æ —Å –ø–æ–º–æ—â—å—é —Å–ª–µ–¥—É—é—â–µ–π –∫–æ–º–∞–Ω–¥—ã: ```bash pnpm install --include=optional sharp ``` # –ù–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞ –æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è –í–∞–º –ø–æ—Ç—Ä–µ–±—É–µ—Ç—Å—è –¥–æ–±–∞–≤–∏—Ç—å –ø–µ—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è –≤ —Ñ–∞–π–ª `.env` –¥–ª—è –ø–æ–¥–∫–ª—é—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –∫ —Ä–∞–∑–ª–∏—á–Ω—ã–º –ø–ª–∞—Ç—Ñ–æ—Ä–º–∞–º: ``` # –û–±—è–∑–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã–µ –ø–µ—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID= DISCORD_API_TOKEN= # –¢–æ–∫–µ–Ω –±–æ—Ç–∞ OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-* # API-–∫–ª—é—á OpenAI, –Ω–∞—á–∏–Ω–∞—é—â–∏–π—Å—è —Å sk- ELEVENLABS_XI_API_KEY= # API-–∫–ª—é—á –æ—Ç elevenlabs GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY= # API-–∫–ª—é—á Gemini # –ù–ê–°–¢–†–û–ô–ö–ò ELEVENLABS ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_multilingual_v2 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STABILITY=0.5 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_SIMILARITY_BOOST=0.9 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_STYLE=0.66 ELEVENLABS_VOICE_USE_SPEAKER_BOOST=false ELEVENLABS_OPTIMIZE_STREAMING_LATENCY=4 ELEVENLABS_OUTPUT_FORMAT=pcm_16000 TWITTER_DRY_RUN=false TWITTER_USERNAME= # –ò–º—è –ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è –∞–∫–∫–∞—É–Ω—Ç–∞ TWITTER_PASSWORD= # –ü–∞—Ä–æ–ª—å –∞–∫–∫–∞—É–Ω—Ç–∞ TWITTER_EMAIL= # Email –∞–∫–∫–∞—É–Ω—Ç–∞ X_SERVER_URL= XAI_API_KEY= XAI_MODEL= # –î–ª—è –∑–∞–ø—Ä–æ—Å–æ–≤ –∫ Claude ANTHROPIC_API_KEY= # EVM EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY # Solana SOLANA_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY SOLANA_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY # Fallback Wallet Configuration (deprecated) WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY=EXAMPLE_WALLET_PUBLIC_KEY BIRDEYE_API_KEY= # API-–∫–ª—é—á –¥–ª—è BirdEye SOL_ADDRESS=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112 SLIPPAGE=1 RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com HELIUS_API_KEY= # API-–∫–ª—é—á Helius ## Telegram TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN= # –¢–æ–∫–µ–Ω –±–æ—Ç–∞ Telegram TOGETHER_API_KEY= ``` # –õ–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω–∞—è –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞ —Å—Ä–µ–¥—ã ### –ù–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞ CUDA –ï—Å–ª–∏ —É –≤–∞—Å –µ—Å—Ç—å NVIDIA GPU, –≤—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏—Ç—å CUDA –¥–ª—è –∑–Ω–∞—á–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–æ–≥–æ —É—Å–∫–æ—Ä–µ–Ω–∏—è –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω–æ–≥–æ –∏–Ω—Ñ–µ—Ä–µ–Ω—Å–∞. ```bash pnpm install npx --no node-llama-cpp source download --gpu cuda ``` –£–±–µ–¥–∏—Ç–µ—Å—å, —á—Ç–æ –≤—ã —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏–ª–∏ CUDA Toolkit, –≤–∫–ª—é—á–∞—è cuDNN –∏ cuBLAS. ### –õ–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã–π –∑–∞–ø—É—Å–∫ –î–æ–±–∞–≤—å—Ç–µ `XAI_MODEL` –∏ —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏—Ç–µ –µ–≥–æ –≤ –æ–¥–Ω–æ –∏–∑ –≤—ã—à–µ—É–∫–∞–∑–∞–Ω–Ω—ã—Ö –∑–Ω–∞—á–µ–Ω–∏–π –∏–∑ [–ó–∞–ø—É—Å–∫ —Å Llama](#run-with-llama). –í—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ –æ—Å—Ç–∞–≤–∏—Ç—å `X_SERVER_URL` –∏ `XAI_API_KEY` –ø—É—Å—Ç—ã–º–∏ ‚Äî –º–æ–¥–µ–ª—å –±—É–¥–µ—Ç –∑–∞–≥—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∞ —Å huggingface –∏ –æ–±—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∞–Ω–∞ –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω–æ. # –ö–ª–∏–µ–Ω—Ç—ã ## –ë–æ—Ç –¥–ª—è Discord –î–ª—è –ø–æ–ª—É—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –ø–æ–º–æ—â–∏ –ø–æ –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–µ –±–æ—Ç–∞ Discord –æ–∑–Ω–∞–∫–æ–º—å—Ç–µ—Å—å —Å –∏–Ω—Å—Ç—Ä—É–∫—Ü–∏–µ–π: [–ù–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞ –ø—Ä–∏–ª–æ–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è –±–æ—Ç–∞](https://discordjs.guide/preparations/setting-up-a-bot-application.html). ### –°–æ–æ–±—â–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ –∏ –∫–æ–Ω—Ç–∞–∫—Ç—ã - [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/elizaos/eliza/issues). –õ—É—á—à–µ –≤—Å–µ–≥–æ –ø–æ–¥—Ö–æ–¥–∏—Ç –¥–ª—è: —Å–æ–æ–±—â–µ–Ω–∏–π –æ–± –æ—à–∏–±–∫–∞—Ö –ø—Ä–∏ –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–∏ Eliza –∏ –ø—Ä–µ–¥–ª–æ–∂–µ–Ω–∏–π –Ω–æ–≤—ã—Ö —Ñ—É–Ω–∫—Ü–∏–π. - [Discord](https://discord.gg/ai16z). –õ—É—á—à–µ –≤—Å–µ–≥–æ –ø–æ–¥—Ö–æ–¥–∏—Ç –¥–ª—è: –æ–±–º–µ–Ω–∞ —Å–≤–æ–∏–º–∏ –ø—Ä–∏–ª–æ–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è–º–∏ –∏ –æ–±—â–µ–Ω–∏—è —Å —Å–æ–æ–±—â–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ–º. ## –ö–æ–Ω—Ç—Ä–∏–±—å—é—Ç–æ—Ä—ã ## –ò—Å—Ç–æ—Ä–∏—è –∑–≤—ë–∑–¥ [![–ì—Ä–∞—Ñ–∏–∫ –∏—Å—Ç–æ—Ä–∏–∏ –∑–≤—ë–∑–¥](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=elizaos/eliza&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#elizaos/eliza&Date)
